title: terrific turkey
directions: Clean and prepare turkey. Pat dry. Rub turkey with butter or margarine; sprinkle lightly with poultry seasoning. Stuff inside cavity with prunes and apricots, about half and half, and large apple, quartered. Place on large sheet of heavy-duty foil. Pour 2 capfuls of apricot brandy over turkey. Roll foil around turkey and seal at top.
Cook at 350° until done.
Baste occasionally. Will be juicy and tender.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix peanut butter and sugar.
By hand, beat in softened ice cream until smooth, but not melted.
Spoon in crust.
Freeze two hours or until firm.
Before serving, drizzle with melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crisco pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut Crisco into flour mixture until of mealy consistency.
Add water, using as little as it takes to make the flour mixture hold together.
Chill for at least 30 minutes (or overnight).
Roll out thin and line pans.
Bake at 425° or fill with filling and bake as directed.

title: meat loaf kids love
directions: Mix by hand the meat, 3/4 of the can of tomato soup, the goldfish, eggs, onion and steak sauce.
Let sit for 10 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°.
Pat into a loaf and bake for 90 minutes. Add the rest of the tomato soup.
Spread on top of the loaf and bake 15 more minutes.
Serve in slices.

title: pizza
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar.
Let stand until bubbly (about 10 minutes).
Add salt and flour (1 cup at a time).
Mix with wooden spoon.
When mixture gets too difficult to stir, use hands and knead into a ball, adding flour as needed.
Divide ball into two. Form into balls and put on floured surface.
Cover and let rise (about 30 to 45 minutes).
Form dough into pizza pan; top with sauce, cheese and favorite toppings.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion together.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients together.
Cover bottom of baking dish with Doritos.
Pour meat mixture over Doritos.
Cover with crushed Doritos.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle cheese on top and melt.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into 1/8-inch slices.
Layer about 1/3 of potatoes in a large roasting pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of flour; dot with 1 stick of butter or margarine that has been cut into 1/4-inch slices and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer potatoes, flour, butter, salt and pepper in two more layers. Cover with milk and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, margarine, Karo and vanilla.
Mix well and add coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Finely crush entire bag of cookies.
Crush until creamy middle disappears.
Cream butter and cream cheese, Add sugar and Cool Whip and mix well.
Combine milk and pudding mix in separate bowl.
When set, add to the cream cheese mixture.
Place half the crushed cookies in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pudding mixture on top.
Add gummy worms in the pudding.
Put remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Can put this in a lined flower pot or sand pail. Refrigerate.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Saute onion and celery in margarine. Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Lightly score the flank steak in a crisscross pattern on both sides and transfer to a large zip lock bag.

title: devil's food cake
directions: *One teaspoon vinegar or lemon juice will sour 1 cup whole milk.

title: flower pot dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies until fine.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, margarine and sugar until smooth.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In the flower pot, alternate layers of cookie crumbs and pudding mixture, ending with crumbs.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Decorate with silk flowers and gummy worms.
Serves 12.

title: baptist pie
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Mash oranges a little.
Add Cool Whip with the milk, pineapple and oranges.
Add the lemon juice last and mix.
Pour into two crusts.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: bubbly beverage:  sparkling apple cider
directions: Combine apple juice concentrate and mineral water, stirring gently.
Serve immediately over crushed ice.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix together just before serving.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and next 5 ingredients.
Spread in round pie pan.
Press shrimp on.
Cover with chopped eggs and chives/onions. Serve with crackers.

title: easy caramels
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in a large, heavy bottom pan.
Bring to a slow boil.
Turn up heat and begin adding milk in a thin stream so that the mixture never stops boiling.
Cook at 242° for about 30 minutes.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not cover until the last half hour of bake time.

title: devil's food float cake
directions: Boil 1/2 cup sugar in 1 1/2 cups water 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and add marshmallows.
Cream butter and the other 1/2 cup sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add nuts and blend.
Drop from large spoon over marshmallows.
Cover dish and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Layer frozen rolls in a Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar, butterscotch pudding and pecans; sprinkle on rolls.
Pour margarine or butter over top.
Cover with a dish towel and let rise overnight at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes after removing from oven; invert on a large round plate.
Spoon any caramel mixture that runs on the plate over top of rolls.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour, sugar and Crisco. Add yeast, then buttermilk.
Work well.
Put in bowl, cover and let rise until doubled.
Shape in rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Cool.
Transfer to medium bowl.
Stir in peppers, mayonnaise, onions and curry powder.
Add peaches and chicken.
Toss lightly.
Line plates with lettuce leaves.
Chill.
Mold salad in center to serve.
Serves 4.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in 1-quart warm water.
Dissolve sugar in 1-quart warm water.
Combine in 1 gallon container:
pineapple juice, Kool-Aid and sugar in gallon container, then finish filling gallon container with water.
Pour this into a container that will hold 2 1/2 to 3 gallons, then add 7-Up.
Freeze overnight (11 to 12 hours).
Take out of the freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving to make it "slushy."

title: strawberry pie
directions: Make a paste of the cornstarch, cold water, sugar and jello. Add 1 cup of boiling water and a few drops of red food coloring. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add 2 tsp. lemon juice and 1 Tbsp. margarine.
Let cool.
Mix with the one quart of strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: mint chip pound cake
directions: Microwave 1/2 cup chips on Medium (50%) for 1 to 2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Combine chocolate with rest of ingredients. Beat 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Fold in remaining 1 1/2 cups mint chips.
Pour into 9-inch round pan.
Microwave at 50% for 3 minutes. Then microwave on High for 3 minutes.
This will use 3 cups batter.
Sprinkle with chocolate powdered sugar.

title: chicken marengoeverton, missouri
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover, simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Uncover, cook to desired consistency.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Heat milk over hot water.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Then pour milk mixture over beaten egg. Return to double boiler until mixture coats spoon.
Add marshmallows and vanilla.
Strain and cool.

title: sunshine citrus punch
directions: Put ice in punch bowl.
Add water and frozen juice concentrates.
Before serving, add ginger ale.

title: witches brew(to serve on halloween)
directions: Combine the apple cider, red hots candies and orange juice. Then add the cloves and allspice. Refrigerate overnight. Strain out spices. When ready to serve, add the ginger ale. Serve hot or cold with ice cubes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed; rinse with warm water.
Add milk, butter and 1/2 of cheese.
Toss gently.
Pour in tomato sauce; stir.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Put rest of cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fabulous dog cookies(for your favorite puppy!)
directions: Mix water and chicken cubes.
Stir in sugar and yeast and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add tomato juice, 1 cup all-purpose flour and wheat germ.
Stir in remaining all-purpose flour and whole wheat flour.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or two 9-inch pans.
In large mixer bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add carrots, oil and eggs; mix until moistened.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Add onion and pepper.
Separately mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans and mix well. Marinate overnight.

title: strawberry jello with walnuts
directions: Make jello according to package directions (substitute 1 cup of pineapple juice for water).
Put in refrigerator and set for a few minutes. Add bananas and walnuts.

title: honey-oatmeal muffins
directions: Add milk, egg, oil and honey to combined remaining ingredients.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moist.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: easy icebox cake
directions: Make chocolate pudding according to directions on box.
Line the bottom of a baking pan with graham crackers (be sure to cover all nooks and crannys with graham cracker).
Cover with a layer of chocolate pudding, then add another layer of graham crackers and so on.
Top layer should be chocolate pudding.
Let cool and refrigerate to set pudding.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Stir egg, pumpkin, 1/3 cup sugar and pumpkin pie spice together.
Spread in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon over pumpkin mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Toss dry stuffing and seasonings with melted butter.
Spread about 2/3 of the mix in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1/3 for the topping.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Flour chops and brown in a little oil.
Brown the onion lightly.
Put pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the onions over the chops.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over the pork chops in the pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
If soup is too thick, thin with a little milk.
Very good gravy.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in saucepan and boil a few seconds.
Pour into greased 13x9x2 baking dish.
Blend granulated sugar and butter.
Sift together flour, baking powder, and cinnamon.
Add alternately with 1 cup milk.
Pour batter over syrup. Bake 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: potatoes anna
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Arrange thinly sliced raw potatoes in 2 or 3 layers.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper; dot generously with butter.
Cover; steam 15 minutes. Uncover; cook until tender and crispy brown on the bottom.
Invert on serving plate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Salt and pepper to taste. Put in a 9 x 13 dish.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, pie filling, eggs and almond flavoring. Mix by hand until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber slices
directions: Mix cucumber and onion, sprinkle with salt, mix well.
Let set in refrigerator 2 hours.
Drain after 2 hours, but don't rinse.
About 1 hour before draining cucumbers, heat sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Pour over cucumbers and onions, mix.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator before using.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the oil, butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir and blend.
Roll a teaspoon of dough into ball.
Press down on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake about 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cheese until creamy.
Add horseradish, Tabasco, Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Blend well.
Fold in green onions and shrimp.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Work this and form into small balls.
I like to make them into ladyfingers.
Cook in moderate oven (325° to 375°) for 30 minutes. Roll tarts in powdered sugar.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Stir sauerkraut with liquid and dressing into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with turkey or corned beef.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Add cheese slices.
Top with bread slices. Brush margarine on bread. Bake uncovered for 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: french strawberry pie
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of pie shell.
Place half of strawberries on cheese.
Mash and strain remaining strawberries (pulp may be used also); bring to boiling point.
Slowly stir in combined sugar and cornstarch.
Continue to stir, cooking slowly to reach boiling point and until mixture thickens.
Cool thoroughly; pour over pie.
Chill and top with cream.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Fry sausage and onion until brown.
Add sauerkraut and bread crumbs.
Blend cream cheese, mustard, garlic salt and parsley.
Add sausage and sauerkraut mixture to cream cheese mixture.
Chill 1 hour or more.
Form into 3/4-inch balls.
Dip in egg and milk mixture and roll in flour.
Fry in deep fat for 30 to 60 seconds. Can be frozen and heated in microwave.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, cook linguine until tender. In small saucepan, heat oil and butter until butter melts.
Add garlic; cook until golden.
Stir in clams with their liquid, oregano, pepper and parsley.
Cook until heated (5 minutes). Drain linguine; return to pot.
Add sauce.
Toss and serve with Romano.
Serves 4.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix everything together and put in a casserole dish.
Bake until fluffy at 325° to 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Melt butter.
Defrost orange juice.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Decorate as desired.
Dip in melted chocolate; roll in powdered sugar. etc.

title: wilma's punch
directions: Combine 2 cups water and sugar in saucepan.
Boil until sugar melts.
In large container, combine jello, pineapple juice, extract and 9 1/4 cups water.
Add sugar water.
Stir well.
May be frozen.
To serve, thaw 4 or more hours before serving.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle half of flour on one side of steak; pound in with meat mallet.
Turn meat and sprinkle with remaining flour, pounding with meat mallet.
Cut into 4 serving size pieces. Arrange in 8-inch square microwave baking dish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over cooled pasta.
Stir.
Better if made a day ahead.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix with bananas, pineapple and strawberries until well combined.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put into rectangular pan and freeze.
Remove from freezer 45 minutes before serving; cut into squares.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box, then pour 1/2 of cake mix into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt package of caramels with milk until soft.
Pour over cooked half of cake.
Then sprinkle chocolate chips over caramels, then 1 cup nuts over chocolate chips.
Pour remaining cake mix over top. Make sure edges are covered.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: jack's breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in 13 x 9-inch greased Pyrex dish.
Then top with sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt together and pour over all.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight before baking.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on top of cake. Place under broiler until topping is bubbly and lightly browned.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Allow to cool somewhat.
Stir dressing into noodles.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste. Delicious served hot or cold.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Add Cool Whip. In another bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla together.
Then mix both parts together.
Place half of the cookies in a foil lined flowerpot.
Add creamed mixture next.
Top with rest of cookies. Garnish with plastic flowers.

title: miss katie's brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken, beef and pork until tender (save the broth). Degrease the broth if you choose.
Mix the chopped onions, meats (cut in small pieces) and bread slices (torn in small pieces). Run through a food chopper.
Put tomatoes through a blender and puree.
After preparing the ingredients, return the broth to your pot on medium heat, and begin adding the ingredients one by one. Stir well as you add each ingredient.
If you need more liquid, add chicken broth or water.
Increase the heat to "high" and stir until the mixture comes to a boil and the onions are well done. It is important that you stir constantly to prevent the mixture from sticking.
Makes about 12 to 13 quarts.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add sugar and mix well.
Add margarine, flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover cake immediately when done with Marshmallow Creme and then the frosting.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, sifted flour, cocoa, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 15 or 20 minutes, or until done, at 325°.
Dampen hands; press marshmallows down on brownies.
Put back in oven until they start to melt.

title: butterhorns(cookies)
directions: Mix butter, flour, sour cream and egg yolk together.
Put in refrigerator and chill so it is workable.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and finely chopped nuts.
Roll part of the dough in pie shape (thin). Put topping on; cut in narrow pie shape slices.
Roll from the outside edge to center and put on baking sheet.
Cookies can be close together as they don't spread.

title: bavarian jello
directions: Mix jello with sugar and 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water and allow to thicken.
Add Cool Whip and mix in well. Refrigerate until served.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In a 1-quart shallow casserole dish, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cups baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in oleo until mixture is the size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls into peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve plain, with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: caroline bowser's german devil's food cake
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
When mixture thickens set aside to cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *May also use leftover turkey.

title: tangy cocktail sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill to blend flavors.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: northern baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain grease.
In casserole, combine remaining ingredients with hamburger.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (until onions are done).

title: aunt diane's cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Chill, divide into 2 or 3 portions, depending on the size of cheese balls you wish to make. Form into balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, cream and broth.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Reduce heat.
Stir in chicken and dash of pepper.
Heat again just to boiling.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with snipped parsley and pimentos, if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit.
Pour instant pudding over fruit and stir gently.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add egg, oil and spices.
Mix well.
Add flour and pour into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: ham cheese wheels
directions: Place one slice of cheese on one slice of meat and roll tightly.
Secure with a toothpick.
Heat in the microwave for about 15 to 20 seconds.
Remove and slice into round disks.
Serve still warm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and paprika.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and paprika. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with stone ground wheat crackers.

title: beef burritos(low-fat)
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, in small pan, prepare rice as directed on label; do not add salt.
Meanwhile, in nonstick 12-inch skillet over high heat, cook ground beef, green pepper and onion until beef is well browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in chili powder and salt.
Cook, stirring 1 minute.
Add beans, tomatoes, corn and cooked rice.
Heat about 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Rinse the chicken well; pat dry and then season chicken with soy sauce, salt and hot sauce; set aside.
In a large, high-walled skillet, heat oil; saute onions, bell pepper and parsley over medium-high heat until onions are clear.
Add wine and stir; add garlic and stir.
Then add chicken.
Mix everything together; then lower the heat to medium.
Cover and cook for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
The chicken should be so tender that it falls apart.
Serve.
Great with steamed rice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in large pan and bring to a rapid boil for 1 minute, no longer. Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups quick cooking oatmeal. Stir well and drop on wax paper. Hardens like fudge. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes lengthwise. Scoop out potato.
Mash with ingredients.
Place back in potato shell. Sprinkle with paprika. Place in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: appetizer meat balls
directions: Mash bread crumbs with milk.
Add meat.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt and add onion.
Toss lightly until ingredients are combined.
Form into 3/4-inch balls.
Brown in butter in skillet. Combine remaining ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Add to meat balls.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens and meat balls are glazed.
Keep warm by serving from chafing dish or some other warming dish.

title: "turkey" roast
directions: Grind scallops and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use an 8 x 12-inch greased baking pan or equal size.

title: choco-scotch clusters
directions: Melt chocolate, butterscotch morsels and peanut butter together in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper or buttered baking sheets.
Let stand in cool place until firm. Yields about 4 dozen confections, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets until tender; peel and slice while hot.
Heat bacon in a skillet.
Add onion and celery; saute until golden.
Heat to boiling the stock and remaining ingredients. Combine all ingredients in skillet.
Gently stir with the potatoes. Serve at once with parsley.
Leftovers can be served chilled. Makes 6 servings.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato into contents of 1 box confectioners sugar with pastry blender or fork until it forms a soft dough.
Sprinkle extra confectioners sugar on board or flat surface.
Divide dough into small pieces and roll out as with pie dough. Dust rolling pin with confectioners sugar.
Spread on as much peanut butter as you like and carefully roll up like a jelly roll.
Place each roll in waxed paper and put in freezer for about 1/2 hour. When cold, slice into pinwheels.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs by hand.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased oblong dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and place marshmallows on top.
Return to oven until marshmallows melt.

title: potato salad
directions: Gently mix all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Butter and bake the sweet potatoes; cut into 1/2-inch pieces or slices. Arrange them in a buttered dish. Mix the sugar, water and butter. Cook on top of stove. Bring to boil and when it makes a very light syrup, pour over potatoes. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients, except cookies.
Blend the two mixtures together.
In a new 6 1/2-inch flowerpot, layer cookies, then mixture.
Continue layering, ending with cookies on top for "dirt." Plant a silk flower or use a drinking straw and a real flower in the center of the flowerpot.

title: baked chicken wings pacific
directions: Combine and heat ingredients; cool.
Pour over wings; marinate 3 hours in refrigerator, turning wings frequently.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, turning and basting.
Drain.
Serve hot or cold.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper. Remove seeds. Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes.
Cook and stir hamburger and onion in 10-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown.
Stir in salt, garlic salt, rice and 1 cup of the tomato sauce and heat through. Stuff each pepper with hamburger mixture.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover.
Cook in a 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: hot cheddar rounds
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Spread mixture on bread and place under broiler 2 to 3 minutes until cheese bubbles.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together 2 c. of sugar and cake flour in a large bowl. Put oleo, crisco, cocoa, and water in a sauce pan and bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and stir.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in a 9x13 in. pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: overnight chicken casserole(yields 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Remove the crusts from bread and set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken; cover with the mushrooms.
In a bowl, beat eggs; blend in milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange cheese on top.
Combine soups and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, crumble crusts; toss with melted butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: batter bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into hot pan in which a small amount of shortening has been heated.
Bake at 375°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Note:
You can use any fruit you like.

title: zucchini and beef italiano
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water 2 or 3 minutes. Drain well. Cook ground beef, onion, garlic and seasonings in skillet until onions are transparent. Stir in cooked rice and tomato sauce. Blend cottage cheese and eggs. Put half of zucchini slices in buttered, shallow two quart casserole; spoon on ground beef mixture. Spread cottage cheese over beef. Top with remaining zucchini. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Place whole chicken in microwave-safe casserole dish.
Baste with butter or margarine.
Season with Season-All, garlic salt and black pepper.
Add onion.
Cover tightly with lid or cling wrap. Cook on High for 20 minutes, with breast down.
Repeat this procedure every 20 minutes, each time turning over chicken and adding seasoning, for about 1 hour.

title: old fashioned cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a skillet (iron is best) or ovenproof baking dish.
Mix together all ingredients and pour in pan.
Cook until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: honey-lemon-dijon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat the egg and milk together in shallow bowl. Dip the chicken pieces in the egg mixture and coat well with bread crumbs. Saute in a large skillet in equal parts of butter or margarine and olive oil as needed, until golden brown. Transfer to baking dish and set aside. Into the skillet, add the honey, lemon juice and Dijon mustard. Whisk over low heat until smooth. Pour over the chicken. Cover the baking pan and bake chicken for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put peanut butter in bowl.
Add melted margarine and mix well. Add powdered sugar until you can no longer mix with your hands. Roll into balls and lay
on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Pour water over top.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Roll fryers in flour and salt.
Brown in oil.
Place in large casserole and pour over the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 2 hours in 325° oven.
Serves 8.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Place in baked	crust
and
cover with meringue made of the 2 egg whites.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine orange juice (heated), butter (melted) and egg.
Mix with dry ingredients and add nuts and sliced cranberries.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding mix, milk, sugar, sour cream and 1/2 of container of Cool Whip. Alternate layer of wafers, bananas and pudding mix. Top with another 1/2 layer of Cool Whip.

title: peas country style
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Garnish with bacon.
Serves 6.

title: iowa sheriff white's grandma's apple pie
directions: Mix lightly and pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Dot with butter. Add top crust.
Bake at 400° until apples are cooked and crust is lightly browned, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: golden raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Beat in egg, water and vanilla.
Combine the oats, flour, orange peel, cinnamon and baking soda.
Gradually add to the cream
mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: 3 fruit punch
directions: Put lemonade, pineapple and strawberries in blender and liquify.
Store in jar in refrigerator until ready to use.
When ready to serve, pour in punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Do not stir punch.
Float strawberries.

title: lobster and seafood fra diavolo
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Blend in peeled garlic and Italian pepper.
Saute until light brown.
Add seafood and braise.
Peel, seed and dice tomatoes.
Simmer with seafood until tender.
Combine basil, parsley and red and black peppers.
Grate fresh Parmesan and Romano cheeses.
Liberally sprinkle 1/2 in skillet and hold remainder for table service. Flavor with sherry to taste.
Add paste.
Reduce heat, stirring constantly.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt Nestle pieces on low heat. Add potatoes and mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper. Chill.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and sour cream.
Stir into mix.
(Dough should be lumpy and soft.)
Drop from tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 large biscuits.
Delicious topped with strawberries or other fruit and whipped cream.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray bottom of muffin pan. Mix all ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 15 minutes, stirring often.
Cream the butter, light brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs and the oats.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs well; gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in potatoes, butter and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar and mix well. Add ground cranberries, pineapple with juice and nuts.
Mix well. Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until set.
Keep chilled.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Microwave bacon about 5 minutes on High, covered.
Add onion and microwave 4 minutes, uncovered, until onions are cooked.
Add rice, black-eyed peas, pepper and 1/2 cup water and jalapeno if desired.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 Oreos into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix pudding as directed on package and fold in cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Pour pudding mixture on top of Oreos.
Crumble remaining 1/2 of Oreos on top.

title: microwave-glazed carrots
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a dish and cover.
Microwave on High
for
to 11 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Mix water and
cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into carrot mixture and cover. Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes.

title: ron's chicken recipe
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper and roll in flour. Brown on both sides in butter.
Arrange in 9 x 12-inch buttered baking dish.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil; remove from heat.
Add flour until it forms a ball.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Spread dough into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Crust will be lumpy and bumpy.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in boiling water until tender (approximately 15 to 20 minutes). Drain carrots. Melt butter. Add syrup, ginger, sugar and orange peel. Stir to mix well and sugar is dissolved. Cool 1 minute. Pour over carrots. Stir until carrots are coated well. Garnish with parsley. Serve warm. Makes 4 servings. Preparation time: 0:45.

title: chicken livers wrapped in bacon
directions: Clean livers.
Cut bacon strip in 3 sections.
Wrap liver in bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn over and bake 1/2 hour on other side.

title: chocolate mint truffles
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in any of the coatings.
Chill 1 hour or until firm. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: rice and peas
directions: Bring water to a boil; stir in bouillon cubes until dissolved. Add all other ingredients.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Let stand, covered, until all water is absorbed. Serves 6 to 8.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add milk slowly; stir thoroughly.

title: spoon yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast in water. Cut Crisco into flour.
Add egg and sugar. Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: corn and burger casserole
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Brown hamburger and onion in skillet. Drain excess grease.
Add potatoes, creamed corn and soup.
Cook on medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: berry mustard
directions: Puree blackberries in a blender until smooth.
Strain seeds. Combine blackberry puree and remaining ingredients in a bowl, whisking until blended.
Serve with pork, wild game or deli meats. Will keep in the refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.

title: dallas cowboy dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Melt butter and cheese in saucepan.
Combine 2 mixtures.
Serve warm with tortilla chips. Makes 5 cups.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together at least 12 hours before you intend to serve.

title: hot caramel apples
directions: In a large heavy bottomed skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter. Add sugar. Stir rapidly just until mixture is golden brown (1 to 2 minutes). Stir in cinnamon. Remove pan from heat. Add milk. Return to heat, stirring until hardened sugar dissolves and mixture looks like caramel (2 to 3 minutes). Add apples and coat with caramel. Cover skillet.
Reduce heat and simmer until apples are just tender (about 5 minutes).
With slotted spoon, transfer apples to serving bowl.
Over high heat, bring caramel to a boil until thickened (1 to 2 minutes).
Pour over apples.

title: blender pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender. Grease 10-inch pie dish. Pour mixture into pie dish. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: oriental wings
directions: Place wings in pan.
Pour soy sauce over wings.
Generously sprinkle with ground ginger.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 or more hours.

title: egg and sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage in a medium skillet and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour into 8 x 11-inch glass baking dish that has been lightly greased. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let it stand a few minutes before serving.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add butter.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients, one at a time.
Stir well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water until done.
Add the 2 tablespoons flour to milk and use a whisk so there's no lumps.
Add to vegetables and water, stirring.
Add Velveeta cheese, cut into small chunks.
Keep stirring until cheese is melted.

title: chrusciki(twist)
directions: Stir yolks and sugar until smooth.
Add sour cream and flavorings.
Sift; measure and sift flour again with salt.
Add to first mixture.
Knead lightly on floured board until firm and smooth enough to roll.
Chill about 1 hour.
Roll out thin and cut in 4-inch strips.
Make a gash in center and pull one end through and fry in deep fat.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Cook until strikes a good boil.
Stir in peanut butter until dissolved. Add corn flakes and drop on waxed paper on cookie sheet.

title: *quest rice
directions: Cook rice and beans or peas, following label directions for each.
Saute garlic and onion in oil until soft.
Mix Ricotta with 3 cups of the Jack or Cheddar cheese.
Mix rice, beans, garlic, onion and chili peppers.
Layer this mixture alternately in a greased, shallow 3-quart casserole with cheese and Ricotta, spreading evenly over casserole.
End with rice mixture.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Place steak in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over steak; cover and marinate in refrigerator for 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove steak, reserving marinade for basting.
Grill 5 inches from hot coals about 4 minutes on each side, turning frequently and basting with marinade.
Serve, slicing across grain into thin slices.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Add the coffee to the water and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat immediately and let stand 2 minutes.
Then strain through very fine strainer or through cheesecloth to remove all grounds. Cool.
Never use leftover regular coffee.

title: san antonio chicken
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon cumin with garlic salt.
Sprinkle on chicken. Brown in oil.
Mix remaining ingredients with the other tablespoon of cumin.
Pour this mixture over the chicken.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes on top of the stove.
Serve over rice.

title: liver lyonnaise casserole
directions: Cut liver into small pieces. Blend flour, salt and pepper. Roll liver in flour mixture; brown on all sides in hot fat in heavy skillet. Remove liver from skillet. Fry potatoes and onions in fat left in skillet until lightly browned and potatoes are tender. Alternate liver and potatoes and onion mixture in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper and pour over top. Cover and bake for 40 minutes in 375° oven. Serves 6.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fry in frying pan until golden brown.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish; add seasonings.
Add all other ingredients and stir.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, tossing every 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towel until cool.
Store in covered container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken and boil; cool.
Debone, breaking chicken into bite size pieces.
Layer the chicken into 2 small or 1 large casserole dish.
Combine soups, milk and chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing over the top.
Bake, covered, until bubbles appear.
Remove cover and brown in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: no milk chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add about 1/4 cup of the water to make a paste.
Beat egg yolks well.
Heat remaining water, margarine and salt.

title: beverly's egg pie
directions: Mix together sausage and Swiss cheese.
Beat eggs and add half and half, onion and green pepper.
Put in bottom of pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Add enough flour to thicken, about 1 1/2 cups. Beat and fry.

title: gomme
directions: Place milk and buttermilk in a kettle.
Beat eggs; add sugar and salt.
Add to milk and cook over low heat for two hours. Thicken with cornstarch.

title: rancher's pecan cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in the egg and extracts.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; gradually add to cream mixture.
Stir in pecans. Roll into 1-inch balls; place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or until set.
Cool for 3 minutes before removing to wire racks.
Yield:
about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: continental casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into a large casserole. Sprinkle crushed potato chips over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: slovenian sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture, blending well.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut and put 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and vanilla, and then add eggs, nuts and apples.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix all together. Bake in a bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done by testing.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: beefed up noodles and beans
directions: Brown steak strips, onion and garlic in skillet in oil.
Add seasonings.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Works best in electric skillet.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Put celery, onion, carrots and 1/4 cup parsley in food processor.
Chop coarse.
Place butter in large frying pan and saute vegetables.
Add corn bread stuffing mix, apples, raisins, creamed soups, lemon and orange juice, walnuts and 1/4 cup parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chicken stock until moist.
Cook 20 minutes covered with tinfoil at 300°.
Remove foil last 10 minutes.

title: biscuits & gravy
directions: Bake biscuits as directed on can.
Put sausage in skillet & brown.
Add flour to sausage & let brown for a few minutes.
Add milk to mixture and stir until thick.
Salt & pepper to taste.

title: turkey vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in large soup kettle.
Add zucchini, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes over medium-high heat.
Add turkey, potatoes, carrots, peas, tomatoes, broth, cumin, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: chicken in a creamy wine sauce
directions: Brown garlic in butter and then add chicken.
Cook chicken until done.
In a bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients. Add these ingredients to the pan with the chicken.
Simmer 5-7 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mother's fudge
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan except vanilla.
Stir until chocolate is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Boil without stirring until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water. Remove from heat; cool.
Beat mixture until creamy.
Add vanilla and pour into greased pan.
Cut into squares while fudge cools.

title: company comin' pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy. Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff. Add sugar and beat again. Roll crackers until fine, chop nuts and add both. Add vanilla and put in greased pie pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 350. Let cool. Spread preserves over this. Spread cool whip over preserves and sprinkle top with coconut.

title: easy chili beans
directions: In skillet brown ground beef and onion.
While this is browning, in a large pot, put 2 cans of tomato sauce and whole tomatoes.
(Blend the tomatoes until liquidy.)
Add salt to taste. Bring to a boil.
When beef is brown, drain all but about 1 tablespoon of grease.
Pour into tomato mixture.
Add chili powder to taste.
(The more powder the hotter the chili!)
Cook about 1 hour.
Add the pinto beans and cook about another 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Using an electric mixer, start mixing the ingredients in the order listed.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake until pie sets at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh garden vegetable soup
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Combine corn and remaining ingredients in a large Dutch oven; cover and bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook fettucine according to package directions.
Drain and return to pan.
Halve pepperoni; add to pasta.
Stir in pizza sauce, 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms, olives and Parmesan cheese.
Transfer to a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.
Kids love it!

title: pasta salad medley
directions: Pour dressing over noodles and marinate in fridge for several hours.
Drain.
Combine salad dressing and cheese; mix well.
Add to noodles and veggies.
Mix and chill.

title: coke and ketchup roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Roll in flour until covered all over.
Heat oil in roasting pan or cast-iron Dutch oven.
Place roast in heated pan and brown on both sides.
Remove roast and remaining oil from pan.
Place roast back in pan.
Pour ketchup and Coke over roast.
Place onion rings and bell pepper rings around and on top of roast.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa real good.
Add milk; stir well. Beat egg yolks, then add to mixture.
Put in double boiler. Cook very
thick, then add oleo and vanilla. Stir well. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until pie shell is done.
Let pie cool, then add meringue. Return to oven. Cook until meringue is golden brown.

title: lindsay and haley magic bars
directions: In a small pan (11 x 7-inch), melt butter.
Set aside.
Crush crackers, then add to butter and spread over bottom of pan.
Add chips, then coconut, then pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl in order listed; mix well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: whipper snaps(cake box cookies)
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonful into bowl of powdered sugar; form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Very good and easy.

title: donuts
directions: Give each child a biscuit to shape as desired.
Put biscuits in hot grease.
Turn once.
Remove from grease and roll in cinnamon and sugar.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium bowl.
Pour into greased 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cooled, top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with finely chopped walnuts, if desired.

title: pineapple grapefruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve from punch bowl with a lemonade ice ring.

title: robert redford cake or four layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool well.

title: leg of lamb, greek style
directions: Put lamb in roaster, fat side up (to remain in this way).
Pour lemon juice over generously.
Season with salt and pepper; now season generously with garlic powder, then onion powder.
Sprinkle top with oregano leaves.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups water to bottom of roaster and put in 500° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° to 350° and cook for remaining time, uncovered.
Last hour, add peeled, quartered potatoes, onions and carrots.
Season and baste. Turn once while cooking.
Make sure there is enough water in pan to make wonderful au jus.

title: date-nut bars
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Continue beating, add sugar gradually.
Fold in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in greased shallow pan (9x9) in 350° oven for 30 - 40 minutes.
Cut in bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mixed bean soup
directions: Soak beans.
Heat oil in stockpot; saute onion and carrot until tender.
Add beans, bones, water, broth, dill and parsley. Bring to full boil, then reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 hours, or until beans are tender.
Remove bones; cut meat from bones and return meat to soup.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Blend strawberries and pineapple juice together.
Then, gradually add chopped up bananas.
Add cream of coconut (however, add preferred measurements).

title: quick corned beef and cabbage
directions: Layer potatoes and onions in greased 3-quart casserole.
Add water, salt, pepper and pickling spices.
Cover and cook on High for 8 to 9 minutes.
Add corned beef and cabbage.
Pour butter over cabbage.
Cover and cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: summer fruit crisp
directions: Preparation:
15 minutes.
Cooking:
25 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a shallow baking dish with 2 tablespoons of the margarine and arrange the fruit in the base.
In the bowl of a food processor, briefly combine the remaining margarine with the flour and sugar until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over fruit.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until top becomes crisp and fruit collapses.
Serve with with creme fraiche.
Serves 6.

title: katrina's guilt-free quiche
directions: Bake pie shell in a 400° oven until pale golden in color.
Do not brown. Remove from oven and cool.
Place layers of Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese, bacon, ham and Parmesan cheese in pie shell.
Beat eggs until frothy and add milk.
Pour custard mixture evenly over pie filling.
Place quiche on baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until set.
Let stand 15 minutes at room temperature before cutting.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Beat egg until light.
Add sugar; mix well.
Mix shortening with cocoa or chocolate; blend.
Sift flour with salt and soda. Add alternately with milk.
Add nuts and chips.
Drop by small portions on greased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: sour cream coconut frosting
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream on high speed of mixer until creamy. Add Cool Whip and 1 package of coconut.
When cake layers have cooled, split and fill with mixture.
Take hands and spread 1 package of coconut on icing.
This is enough icing for a 4 layer cake.
This cake can be frozen and kept in the freezer until ready to cut.
Let set on plate a few minutes to thaw.

title: shawn's red hot chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Then add green pepper, onion and banana pepper.
Saute until soft.
Put in a large pot and then add tomatoes, chili beans, chili powder, cumin, cocoa, cinnamon and cayenne pepper.
Cook on low heat, stirring occasionally for 2 hours.

title: yogurt onion dill dip
directions: Blend or whip by hand.
Chill.
Enjoy with raw vegetables.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat in roaster or broiler pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour 1/4 cup teriyaki sauce over top.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Remove from oven and pour 1/2 cup cooking sherry over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mushroom sauce over top and mushroom soup.
Pour tap water around meat.
Cover pan with tight fitting lid or seal with heavy-duty foil.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 4 hours.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine carrots, soup and cheese; pour into a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Mix crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa in a saucepan and boil for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonful on wax or foil paper.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: heavenly lime salad
directions: Dissolve one large gelatin in 2 c. boiling water in large mixing bowl.
Mash cream cheese in small bowl.
Add hot gelatin mixture & stir until dissolved.
Melt 18 marshmallows in 1/4 c. boiling water on top of double boiler.
Then add gelatin mixture & 1/2 c. whipped cream.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Add pineapple & 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into large baking dish.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend butter and two sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Mix soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons.
Decorate with 3 or 4 M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to creamed mixture.
Beat well. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot spicy cider
directions: Makes 20 cups in large coffee pot.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter together well.
Press this in long cake pan with
your
fingers
with just a little up on the sides and end.
Mixture
will
be
sticky.
Next mix eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat good and pour over cake mix. Bake at 275° to 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: angel lush
directions: Mix the dry pudding and pineapple in medium bowl. Stir in Cool Whip. Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers. Place bottom layer of cake, cut side up, on serving plate. Spread 1 1/3 cups of pudding mixture onto the bottom layer. Cover with middle cake layer and spread 1 cup of mixture on top. Top with remaining layer and top with remaining mixture. Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Garnish with berries.

title: krispie roll
directions: Cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Press mixture firmly into a buttered jelly roll pan (15 x 3/4-inch).
Melt 1/3 cup butter with milk over low heat.
Sift in icing sugar and cocoa.
Blend thoroughly.
Remove Rice Krispies from pan.
Spread evenly with cocoa mixture. Starting at one end, roll up to form log.
Wrap in greased wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Tomatoes may be dipped in boiling water, cooled and peeled, or may be washed and put through a food processor or blender with peeling on.
In a large kettle, saute onions in olive oil until transparent (do not brown).
Add tomatoes.
Bring to boil; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Put through sieve or food mill. Return juice to kettle, adding remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until thick and mixture rounds on spoon (usually takes longer).
Pour into hot pint or quart jars; adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 20 minutes.
Start counting time when water in canner returns to boiling.
Makes about 10 pints.
When ready to use, add 1 small can tomato paste per pint to 1 pound ground beef.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and egg in double boiler until sauce is very thick; add butter, stirring well.
Cool; mix pineapple, marshmallows and walnuts into sauce.
Pour into serving dish; chill.
Yield 8-10 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: By hand, combine egg, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork to make crisscross pattern.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until edges are slightly brown and cookie centers are set, but not brown.
Watch carefully.
Let cool on rack.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: carrot cake *
directions: Beat the sugar, Wesson oil, eggs and hot water about 210 strokes.
Fold in flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, soda and salt.
Then add black walnuts and carrots.
Bake at 250° for 55 minutes in a tube pan.

title: crab chowder
directions: Heat the milk.
Add the remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
A hefty lunch. Serve with breadsticks.

title: old fashioned butter rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine flour, shortening and buttermilk in the bowl of food processor, fitted with the steel blade. (Or make the biscuit dough in your usual way.) Process until dough forms. Remove from bowl onto a well-floured surface. Knead until dough is a little firmer than regular biscuit dough. Roll out to a rectangle about 9 x 13 inches. Spread the 6 tablespoons of softened (not melted) butter over dough and sprinkle with 5 to 6 tablespoons sugar. Roll up jelly-roll fashion starting with the 13 inch side. Cut into pinwheels that are about 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick. Place cut side down in a buttered 9x13x2 inch baking pan.

title: pine cone bird feeders
directions: Stir together peanut butter and room temperature margarine. Cover pine cones with this mixture.
Next, roll pine cones in bird seed.
Tie string around pine cone and hang outside.
A discarded Christmas tree makes a great feeder.

title: tempters
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook 1 minute.
Remove from stove; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon on wax paper or plate.
Let cool.

title: loaded mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven and cover with water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until tender.
Drain and place in mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat on medium-low speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in 2 cups cheese, bacon and onions.
Transfer to greased 3 qt. baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Yield: 14 servings.

title: mt. dew cake
directions: Mix all together, except nuts. Place nuts in bottom of Bundt pan. Pour batter on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Stew chicken, reserving stock (6 cups).

Remove meat from bones in coarse pieces. Cook onion, pepper and mushrooms in butter until soft but not brown. Add liquid from mushrooms and olives to stock and bring to a boil. Add noodles and cook until tender. Add chicken, onion and pepper mixture, then add remaining ingredients except cheese.

title: super bowl chicken
directions: Put chicken breasts in shallow pan and cover with soy sauce. Marinate chicken breasts in soy sauce for 10 minutes for 2 (30 minutes for 15 to 20 chicken breasts).
The longer you leave in soy sauce, the saltier it will get.
Grill on barbecue until chicken is no longer pink inside but still juicy, about 20 minutes depending on how many chicken breasts you have on grill.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Beat cream cheese with fork until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple.
Add 1 cup of chopped pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Serve with Leibniz crackers or your favorite cracker.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and onion until crisp.
Add flour; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes and eggs.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over hot, sliced boiled potatoes.
Add 2 sliced boiled eggs.
Serve warm.
Can prepare a day ahead.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix softened braunschweiger, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish together and form into a ball.
Put ball into freezer.
Let stand until it stiffens (about 2 hours).

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place breasts in casserole dish with water.
Dot with margarine and bake, uncovered, until done.
(Have rice cooked.) Take chicken out of dish; pour drippings in with soup.
Blend well.
Put chicken with rice back in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and rice.
Bake until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar well.
Add egg and All-Bran. Sift dry ingredients.
Mix nuts with flour.
Add alternately with bananas and water.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in greased loaf pan. Let stand 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Soften ice cream in a large bowl.
Don't let it get soupy, just to stirring consistency. Crush cookies with rolling pin and add to ice cream. Add Cool Whip and pecans. Stir to mix completely.
Put in a tube pan.
Freeze. Remove from pan and store in freezer.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add pineapple, coconut, melted margarine and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake 1 hour until brown at 300°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Pour hot water over apples.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Cut in margarine until like a coarse meal.
Sprinkle over apples and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: Combine Zesty Italian dressing, soy sauce, garlic, ginger, pepper and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add chicken strips and let marinate at least 4 hours.
When chicken has marinated, cook onion, green or red pepper, carrots, squash or zucchini and broccoli or cauliflower in a large skillet or wok in about 2 to 3 tablespoons butter or vegetable oil.
Cook until desired tenderness; set aside.
In same skillet, brown chicken. Add cooked chicken to vegetables and serve over rice.
Add more soy sauce, if desired.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate.
Add flour, which has been sifted with soda and salt, alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch layer pans, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet barbecue pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 10 pork chops.
Spoon sauce over chops and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Take a medium size eggplant and slice thin, about 1/8-inch thick.
Place sheets on paper towels.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.

title: light 'n lean chicken
directions: Spray nonstick frypan with reduced calorie vegetable cooking spray.
Heat to medium temperature.
Add chicken and sprinkle with 1/4 tablespoon of the pepper.
Cook, turning, about 20 minutes or until brown on all sides.
Reduce temperature to low.
Add garlic halves and continue cooking until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease, about 10 minutes more.
Remove chicken to warm plate, leaving garlic in pan.
Add chicken broth and wine.
Over high temperature, bring to a boil.
Continue boiling about 5 minutes. Reduce temperature to low.

title: dill pickles fresh kosher style
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Make a brine of vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a boil.

Place a generous layer of dill, 1/2 to 1 clove of jars. Pack cucumbers into the jars. When jars are half filled with cucumbers, add another layer of dill and complete the packing of the jars. Fill the jars to within 1/2-inch of the top with the brine. Put caps on jars, screwing the band on tight. Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: bubbling biscuits bits
directions: Place butter or margarine in oven at 350° to melt, about 5 minutes. Mix together rest of ingredients. Open 1 package (8 ounce) refrigerated buttermilk biscuits. Cut each biscuit into 4 equal pieces. When butter or margarine is melted, remove pan from oven.

title: bean 'n beef pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, half of the onions, the bread crumbs, 1/4 cup of soup, the egg, thyme leaves, salt and pepper. Press mixture evenly against the sides and bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Turn beans into meat-lined pan; spread remaining soup over beans and bake uncovered for 25 minutes.
Arrange remaining onions on top; bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes, then cut into wedges.

title: chocolate chip nut bars
directions: Blend sugar, flour and butter until resembles coarse crumbs. Remove 1 cup. To remaining mixture add baking powder, salt, vanilla, milk and egg. Mix until smooth. Butter 9 x 13-inch pan. Pat batter in pan; spread evenly. Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top evenly, then sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until cake pulls away from sides of pan and tests done in center with toothpick.

title: almond delight truffles(a microwave recipe)
directions: In microwave-safe 2 quart bowl, beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs, almond extract, honey and vanilla, stirring until well combined. Stir in cereal, cocoa and coconut.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, turning dish 1/4 turn halfway through.
Remove from microwave and stir immediately until well blended.
Let cool to room temperature.
Shape into balls. Roll each ball in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and nuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water. Add thawed raspberries to the mixture while still hot.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool until syrupy.
Pour Jell-O-raspberry mixture over cooled crust.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Melt over hot water the marshmallows with the milk; let cool.
Fold in whipped topping; spread over top of set Jell-O-raspberry mixture. Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: deep south chicken casserole
directions: Prepare Minute rice to serve six people in chicken broth. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread broccoli over rice.
Spread chicken over broccoli.

title: potato roll dough
directions: Mix in order given, using enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 5 minutes.
Let rise until doubled.
(Or it can be refrigerated up to 5 days.)
Punch down.
Shape into rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: layered antipasto salad(yields 8 servings)
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade. Set aside artichokes.

title: meat loaf, the best
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery for 10 minutes.
Mix with meat. Add beef bouillon, garlic powder and basil.
Mix and taste; add salt, if needed.
Add egg(s) and mix.
Use a glass baking dish; form mixture into a long loaf (3-inches) high or so.
Place pepper, onion, celery and basil around and on top of mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with tinfoil, don't let tinfoil touch mixture.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Check after 1 1/2 hours and remove tinfoil.
Let it brown the last 1/2 hour.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place beef in a small baking pot with a tight lid.
Add tomato juice, bay leaf, all vegetables and salt.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, adding additional tomato juice if needed. Bake longer if needed, until meat is very tender.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover
x 15-inch
pan with crushed graham crackers. Keep 1 cup.
Slice
bananas and layer over crumbs.
Slice ice cream
in 1/2-inch
slices
and place over bananas.
Sprinkle nuts on ice cream and freeze until firm.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix together cake flour, baking powder, milk, shortening, 1 cup sugar and salt.
Put in greased 9 x 12-inch (or smaller) pan. Pour over the topping.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 layer cake pans, dividing batter equally in the 3 pans.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched.
Spread the filling on top and between layers.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Melt butter and blend in sugar.
Mix in beaten eggs and mashed bananas, blending until smooth.
In a bowl, stir together all-purpose flour until thoroughly blended.
Add dry ingredients alternately with hot water.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: miniature quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate each biscuit by peeling layers. (It helps to spray hands with Pam.)
Use each layer to line one section of a miniature tart pan.
Combine cheese, meat and onions; mix well.
Spoon a teaspoon of mixture into each section of biscuit lined tart pan.
Stir together eggs, sour cream, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour 1 tablespoon of mixture into each tart. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Skin and bone chicken breast halves.
Place chicken breasts in a skillet. Sprinkle with pepper. Combine chicken broth and white wine. Add to skillet.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and dot with slices of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange pineapple chunks over cherries; sprinkle with cake mix.
Cover with melted butter or margarine; top with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious served hot or cold.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, syrup, oleo, cream of tartar and salt to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add baking soda. Pour over the popped corn, mixing thoroughly.
Put in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 200°.
Put on waxed paper and separate the corn into small clumps.
Store in an airtight container.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
(Watch it, it wants to burn.)

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour. Add milk. Cook over medium heat until it begins to thicken. Remove from heat. Add salt and pepper, onion, if desired, and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted. Put already cooked macaroni in casserole dish and pour in all ingredients, already mixed. Stir thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together macaroni shells, cabbage, pimento and carrots.

title: crazy ruby's baked alaska
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
In large mixer bowl blend brownie mix, eggs and 1/4 cup water for 1/2 minute on medium speed.
Add remaining water; beat 1 minute.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan; spread evenly.
Bake in preheated oven of 350° for 14 to 16 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Lift gently from pan and cool on rack completely.
Cut into 3 equal lengthwise strips.
Spread 1 strip with mint ice cream and another strip with vanilla ice cream. Stack one on top of the other and top with plain strip of brownie. Cut in half crosswise.
Wrap each half in heavy-duty foil.
Freeze quickly.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 18 (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin pan cups.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, oats, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and pecans.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly; stir in zucchini and salad oil.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Spoon batter into muffin pan cups.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden and toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Immediately remove muffins from pan.
Serve warm or cool on wire rack and serve later.
Reheat, if desired.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, mushrooms, parsley, vinegar, bouillon and tomato paste.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream until heated.
Serve over noodles prepared according to package directions.

title: deep dish lobster
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese, in a bowl.
Put in six 8-ounce casseroles; top with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, or until real hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as per package directions.
When cake comes out of oven, poke holes in it with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour butterscotch or caramel ice cream topping over the cake.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle four crushed Heath bars over the top and refrigerate.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Combine water and corn meal; fix as for mush.
Brown hamburger and onion in fat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Alternate layers of corn meal mush and meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: easy eggs benedict
directions: In a saucepan, combine the soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice.
Heat, stirring now and then.
Place a slice of ham on each muffin half, then top with poached egg.
Pour sauce over eggs and serve.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushrooms.
Stir in mushrooms. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 1 1/3 cups dip.

title: cheese struedel
directions: Grease foil on cookie sheet.
Lay out 1 package of rolls. Pinch seams together.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks together until smooth.
Spread over layer of crescent rolls.
Cover with second package of rolls, pinched together and all edges sealed.
Brush with whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Tear off bone into bite-sized pieces.
Make stuffing according to package.
Alternate stuffing, chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° until golden brown in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: swiss elk steak
directions: Dredge elk steak lightly in flour; shake off excess.
Melt butter in a large skillet; brown steak on both sides.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Combine the next 8 ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cooked to desired tenderness.
If desired, place cheese over steak before serving.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: mustard grilling sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Brush on chicken or pork while grilling.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Add salt to taste. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Cover and cook slowly until done.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In greased dish, place asparagus; sprinkle on onion and cheese.
Spread on undiluted soup.
Sprinkle on chopped eggs.
Dot with butter; sprinkle croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Simmer in stock after chicken is removed the onion and green pepper for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Dip tortillas in stock.
Line bottom of pan.
Layer chicken, onion and green pepper and cheese. Pour cans of soup and tomatoes over it.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Freezes well when uncooked.

title: biscuit dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Stir in milk, blending with fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful into broth.
If preferred, knead on floured surface 10 to 12 strokes; roll 1/2-inch thick and into 6 x 4-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Plump raisins by soaking in water or rum, slightly heated for about 5 minutes.
Drain and save 1 cup liquid.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add 1 cup raisin water and dry ingredients alternately.
Add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/2 package taco mix, 1 jar salsa and green chilies.
Mix all together.
Shape into a circle.
Top with Cheddar cheese and black olives; the other jar of salsa can be put on after you shape into a circle, then add cheeses and olives. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: After potatoes boil, cool and peel, then grate on large grater.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix soup, 1 cup of cheese, 1/2 cup melted butter, green onions and sour cream.
Add grated potatoes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cornflakes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chicken continental
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Put rice in bottom of dish. Mix the last five ingredients and pour 1/2 of the mixture over the rice.
Place chicken on top of the rice and pour the remaining mixture over the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Remove the foil and top with shredded cheese.
Put back in oven, uncovered, for approximately 5 minutes to melt the cheese.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Prepare nuts and pretzels.
Melt chocolate (can be done in microwave), then grease pan.
Pour into pan.
Let set.
Cut or break into pieces.

title: elmer fudd pucker
directions: Mix all together. Serve in large glass filled with ice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil the water and sugar for 5 minutes.
