Add the cranberries; cook 5 minutes or until the cranberries pop.
Dissolve the jello in 1/2 cup boiling water; add to the mixture.
Add mixture.
Add 1 cup pecans.

title: african chow mein(servings:  4)
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over top.
Bake at least 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Top with slivered almonds.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dough onto large cookie sheet; bake 8 minutes at 350°. While this is cooling, mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and powdered Ranch dressing.
Spread mixture on bread crust.
Grate broccoli and cauliflower (any vegetables) and sprinkle generously over crust.
Use pimento for garnish.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Add milk, filling and butter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: minnesota minestrone
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic until brown and drain off the fat.
Place this and all other ingredients in a large pot (except macaroni).
Heat to boiling; then reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Add macaroni and continue until it is tender.

title: golden cheddar garlic bread(good served with chili)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise and garlic powder to taste.
Spread mixture over entire cut surface of French bread halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes until bubbly and golden.
Let stand 2 or 3 minutes before slicing into 2-inch servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Sift flour, salt and pepper together and work grated cheese and margarine into dry mix. Add chopped nuts. Make into rolls and chill overnight or freeze. Slice thin and bake at 350° until lightly colored.

title: apple cinnamon yams
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Thinly slice yams and layer alternately with apples.
Mix orange juice, brown sugar, lemon juice, salt and cinnamon.
Pour over apples and yams.
Cover and microwave on High 15 minutes, basting several times during cooking.
Dot top of yams with butter and sprinkle with pecans. Microwave uncovered 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: crab mold
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine soup, cheese and onion.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring.
Blend in mayonnaise; remove from heat.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a bowl. Make into 1-inch balls. Put in 8 x 8 baking dish. Mix tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire; pour over meatballs. Cover and bake 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 more minutes. Enjoy.

title: white mountain goliath sandwich
directions: Slice bread loaves in half horizontally.

Spread one slice of each loaf with mustard and the other slices with mayonnaise. Dividing evenly between loaves, layer ham slices, then American cheese slices, turkey slices, Swiss cheese slices and roast beef slices.
(At this point, you may wrap the sandwiches in plastic wrap and microwave until cheeses are melted, if you like.)
Add tomato slices (and lettuce and onion, if desired) immediately before you slice into wedges for serving.
Serve with your favorite chips and beverages.
Add a dessert of fresh fruit for a complete meal for four hearty appetites.

title: lewis and clark white chili
directions: Cook onion and garlic in olive oil until onion is tender. Stir in cumin, oregano, ground red pepper and cloves. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Add beans, peppers and chicken stock or broth. Bring to boil and reduce heat to simmer. Add chicken. Simmer for about a half hour or the beans are very tender.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Remove from oven. Set aside.
Combine sugar and water in saucepan. Cook over moderate heat until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat. Set aside.
Place flour in bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture is consistency of coarse crumbs.
Add milk.
Stir with fork just until dough leaves sides of bowl. Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead just until smooth.
Roll out into 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Place apples in small bowl. Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Toss lightly to mix. Spread apples evenly over dough. Roll up, jelly roll fashion, from long side. Moisten edge with water.
Pinch to seal. Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place slices, cut sides down, over butter in baking pan.
Pour sugar syrup over top. Bake 1 hour.

title: henderson house cold peach soup
directions: Put the peaches, sour cream or yogurt and extract in blender or food processor and blend well. If canned peaches are used, you may need to add 1 to 2 teaspoons of the syrup so the mixture will not be too thick. The finished soup should be about the consistency of thick cream.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Slice carrots crossways or diagonally and cook until tender (2 pounds makes 1 1/2 to 2 quarts).
To make sauce, cook together.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with margarine and milk; pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramels.
Pour remaining cake batter on top of chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 20 more minutes at 250°, then for 10 more minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: quick easy gingerbread
directions: Mix the oil, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Add flour and spices, mixing well, then add boiling water and mix again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (325° for glass baking dish).

title: bow ties with cream sauce and mushrooms
directions: Saute all ingredients, except cream, pasta and cheese, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions in salted water.
Add cream to other ingredients and simmer until pasta is cooked.
Drain pasta and mix with sauce and cheese.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; stir and add to cooled milk.
Add one-half of flour and 2 tablespoons of the sugar.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, about 1/2 hour.

title: sego tamale pie
directions: Mix
together
in
saucepan, stir and boil until thick. Cool while preparing meat mixture.

title: brown sugar fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into bowl.
Add brown sugar, shortening, 2/3 of buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes, medium on mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add rest of buttermilk, eggs and melted chocolate.
B eat 2 more minutes.
Pour into prepared pans.
Pan Size:
two 9-inch round layers or 13 x 9-inch oblong.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers and 40 to 45 minutes for oblong.

title: frijoles vaguerso(soup)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Next day, add soda and fresh water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Drain and wash well under hot water.
Add ham hocks and water to cover.
Cook on low heat for about 2 hours. Add water, if needed.
Remove bone and fat.
Cut ham in pieces and return to pot.

title: peach pudding
directions: Drain peach juice and save.
Cook fruit and 1/2 cup sugar over low heat.
While making everything else, melt 1/2 stick margarine in baking pan.
Mix sugar, baking powder, flour and milk.
Drop dough by spoonfuls over melted butter; add fruit, then pour drained peach juice over all.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Let margarine and cheese come to room temperature, then mix. Add flour, salt and soup mix.
Leave overnight in refrigerator. Make into marble size balls.
Push down with fork; bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Refrigerate cherries before coating with chocolate.
If desired, soak cherries in brandy 3 to 5 days (whiskey can also be used).

title: taco pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Add 1/2 package of seasoning.
Roll out pizza crust in a pizza pan.
Mix pizza sauce and remaining seasoning.
Spread on crust.
Add meat on top of sauce evenly.
Sprinkle cheese on top and sprinkle onions and olives on cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until crust is done.
Then serve.

title: molasses coffee bars
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add coffee and molasses.
Dissolve soda in warm water and add.
Stir well.
Add salt, ginger, cloves and cinnamon to mixture.
Add 2 cups of flour; mix well.
Add rest of flour and don't stir too much.
Spread 1/4-inch thick in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes
until lightly browned.

title: wheat salad
directions: Place wheat in bowl and cover with water.
Let soak 4 hours or overnight.
Drain and place wheat in slow cooker.
Cover with water about one inch above wheat and cook on low heat for 5 hours. (Do not boil.)
Drain, rinse, and cool.
When cold, mix together cream cheese, pineapple, lemon juice and pudding mix.
Add wheat and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and serve.

title: chicken delish
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Evenly spread diced chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Spread over chicken.
Top with crushed stuffing mix and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Pour half into prepared tube pan.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half over batter.
Pour in remaining batter and repeat with remainder of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast half on a sheet of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place 1 slice of ham and cheese in center of each chicken piece. Sprinkle evenly with parsley and pepper; roll up lengthwise and secure with a wooden toothpick.
Dip each chicken breast in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken to a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to reserved drippings and stir well.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Cut approximately 1-inch thick slice from top of potatoes. Scoop out pulp into mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients except paprika.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon into shells.
Top with strips of Velveeta; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Bring rice, onion, green pepper, soup and water to a boil.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix in sausage. Pour entire mixture into an 8-inch square casserole dish.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, mushroom soup, half the cracker crumbs, egg, onion, half the cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper, water chestnuts and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs and cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by spoonsful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican taco casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, and green pepper.
Drain.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, seasonings and enchilada sauce.
Alternate layers of meat, tortillas, sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cocoa snuggles
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips in water.
Stir constantly until smooth.
Slowly add milk, cream and salt.
Heat through, but don't boil.
Add Schnapps just before serving. Garnish each mug with whipped cream and peppermint stick stirrer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cool; add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Pour filling into pie shell and top with pecans.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; stuff into shells.
Lay in single layer in baking pan.
Mix picante sauce with water and pour over stuffed manicotti.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese, return to oven to melt cheese.
Serve over shredded lettuce with sour cream, sliced black olives, green onions, diced tomatoes and jalapenos, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and crust together.
Pour 2 cups pecans into pie crust.
Pour pie mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Marinate chicken at least one hour.
Add sesame seed if desired.

title: potatoes elegante
directions: Rinse potatoes; dry on paper towels.
Brush 1 tablespoon margarine onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Coat potatoes with remaining margarine. Arrange single layer of potatoes on bottom and sides of pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Invert immediately onto serving plate.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Cover bulgur with water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and drain.
Cool.
Combine with chopped parsley, green onions and tomatoes.
Stir together cinnamon, salt, lemon juice and olive oil. Pour over salad and stir.

title: wedding meat balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Combine tomato juice, chili powder, onion, sauce and sugar in saucepan. Cook for 30 minutes.
Drop meat balls in boiling sauce and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: dianne's cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir in condensed milk until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well, then add lemon juice to taste (more will make it taste tarter).
Divide into two 8-inch graham cracker pie crusts.
Top with fruit pie filling of choice.
May make own crust if desired.
Place in refrigerator until chilled throughout before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses with milk in mixer.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Turn out onto Saran Wrap and mold into ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: cheese dip
directions: Pour Ro-Tel in saucepan.
Add cheese and pepper; cook on heat until cheese is melted.
For spicy taste, add pieces of cooked sausage or hamburger.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into bottom of 13 x 9-inch or jelly roll pan, ungreased.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool completely.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, 1/2 of onion soup mix, bread crumbs, milk and egg.
Shape into 4 patties.
Brown in skillet in shortening. Add remaining soup mix and flour; gradually stir in water and mushrooms.
Cover and cook over low heat 25 minutes, stirring now and then.
Serves 4.

title: easy, fast and delicious chocolate cake
directions: Bring water and cocoa to boil in large saucepan, then add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Then add eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° in 11 x 19-inch pan for 20 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet and combine.
Put in greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in medium saucepan; bring to a boil while stirring to dissolve sugar.
Set aside to cool.
In large bowl or covered Tupperware bowl, combine next 6 ingredients. Pour cooled liquid over the vegetables.
Let marinate at least 12 hours. Stir occasionally.
This stays good several days.

title: ernie's chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together the soup and sour cream.
Get a pan and sprinkle corn flakes on bottom (even layer).
Dunk chicken in the soup and sour cream mix and place in pan.
After placing all the chicken in pan, sprinkle with remaining corn flakes.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour melted butter over top of chicken.
Return to oven and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: baked beans(microwave)
directions: Cook bacon for 4 minutes.
In large glass casserole, mix bouillon, Worcestershire, mustard, brown sugar, catsup and onion; add beans.
Stir well.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and place around edge.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 9 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: sunshine broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and raisins.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Add eggs to mashed sweet potatoes and blend well with hand mixer.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter, salt and cinnamon; blend with mixer.
Add some orange juice, if mixture is dry and pasty, to moisten.
Smooth out mixture in casserole dish. Top with nuts and remaining brown sugar (may not need all of brown sugar), then drizzle top with remaining melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots very thin.
Cook until just tender in unsalted water.
Do not overcook. Drain well.
Add tomato soup and stir.
Combine all other ingredients and add.
Chill overnight. This can be kept for two to three weeks.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, butter
and milk in a small pan and boil for 3 or 4 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.
Put in small mixing bowl and beat.
When it looks thick and creamy, let set for 30 seconds.
If it piles on your finger, it is ready!

title: stuffed tomato
directions: Using spoon, scoop out insides of tomato.
Mix with cornbread, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff in tomato shell. Refrigerate.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Cream the cheese with juice from the pineapple.
Whip up Dream Whip and set aside.
Boil the orange juice and dissolve jello. Add the sherbet and stir until melted.
Add other ingredients. Chill until set.

title: cheese burst biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Partially separate each biscuit into 2 layers; insert 1 cheese cube.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press edge to seal well.
Cut a deep X on top of each biscuit.
Brush with milk; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars.
Cream.
Add egg.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Make a crisscross pattern.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: congealed pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil on stove.
Stir in jello, reduce heat to low and simmer about 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions.
Add Dream Whip, cottage cheese and pecans to jello mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: antipasto
directions: Serve with chips or rye chips.

title: steve gordon's chicken with grapes
directions: Pound chicken breasts between plastic wrap until 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper mixture. Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Quickly brown chicken (add additional pepper, if desired).
Remove chicken from skillet when browned on both sides (need not be completely cooked); keep warm.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a deep dish.
Beat together the sugar, flour and milk until smooth.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir. Pour fruit over the batter the sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: fun pizza
directions: Take a slice of bread, spread with 1 tsp of pizza sauce, sprinkle your favorite topping and finish with sprinkling some cheese.
Put it in the toaster oven and let it bake for 5 minutes or until crispy.
To make whole lot at one time put it on pizza pan and bake in the oven until crispy and cheese is melted.

title: individual fruit cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs (one at a time) and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and sherry alternately (very small amounts of sherry at a time).
Save 3/4 cup of flour to coat fruit and nuts.
Add fruit and nuts last.
Bake in small muffin tins, greased and floured or use paper cups.
Fill tins or cups 3/4 full and bake in a 275° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Drop a few drops of sherry on each cake while hot.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: dump pie
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over ingredients.
Stir slightly. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle water over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine broth, margarine, salt and peppers.
Bring to boil. Process or grind all meat, corn and tomatoes.
Add to broth, a little at a time, stirring.
Be careful not to let stick or burn. Simmer slowly for 5 to 6 hours.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
This sauce is good for beef, pork and chicken; and can be used for kabobs or barbecue. Mix meat with marinade sauce in bag or bowl turning every few hours until ready to cook.

title: peachy waffles
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix until blended.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Add fruit to melted butter.
Combine milk, flour and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well, adding flavoring and eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Blend in nuts and pour mixture into greased and floured pan.
Put in cold oven and set at 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes one large pan or 10 small cakes. Bake small cakes for 1 hour.
Leave 1-inch space between small pans.
Fill about 1/2 full.

title: zucchini tomato soup
directions: In a skillet saute zucchini and onion in oil until tender. Sprinkle with salt.
Add the V8 juice, tomato, pepper, and basil. Cook until heated through.
Garnish with cheese and bacon if desired.
Serves 2.

title: mock cherry pie
directions: Let the first 3 ingredients come to a boil until cranberries are almost cooked. Add the flour, sugar and vanilla to other mixture. Cook until thick. Makes filling for 1 pie.

title: bar-x-sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese slices, and spread on bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and place cheese slices on top.
Return to oven until cheese slices melt.

title: waffle fry nachos
directions: Bake fries according to package directions.
Transfer to a 10 inch ovenproof skillet.
Top with the bacon, onions, olives, tomatoes, salsa and cheeses.
Return to the oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: corn and pea salad
directions: In a pan, heat vinegar, oil and sugar until sugar melts. Pour this over vegetables.
Serve cold.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg whites until stiff.
Take remaining ingredients and mix in separate bowl, then fold in peaches to egg whites.
Pour in ice cream freezer; fill with milk remaining way.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Fry chicken, onion and garlic in a little oil.
In a saucepan, stir cornstarch with broth.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in 1 cup cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and parsley.
Remove 1 cup sauce.
Stir chilies into chicken mixture.
Spoon chicken mixture evenly into 12 tortillas, roll up and place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Freezes well unbaked.

title: sausage mac
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water for about 8 minutes or until just tender; drain.
Cook meat and onion until meat is browned; drain fat.
Add corn, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in cream cheese and milk.
Stir in macaroni and heat through.
Makes 2 servings.
(Adaptable for one.)

title: bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a large pot.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain beans and rinse.
Cover with water and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until beans are tender.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into a ball.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add soup, mix with pimento and milk.
Cover with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat to serve.

title: baked squirrel 1
directions: Coat the squirrels with salt and prepared flour and brown in oil in a baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Reduce heat and cook an additional 45 minutes.

title: microwave lemon meringue pie
directions: In a 2 quart casserole, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Blend in water and food coloring.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Separate eggs.
Set egg whites aside.
Blend a small amount of the hot mixture into the egg yolks, gradually adding all of mixture.
Cook on medium for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once.
Remove and add butter, juice and rind; stir to melt butter and blend.
Pour into baked pastry.
Make meringue by beating 3 egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Gradually beat in 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread over filling and microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until set.
Meringue will not brown in the microwave.
If desired, brown in conventional oven set at 375° for about 8 minutes. Or cool filling and top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to full boil for 1 minute stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.
Pour immediately over cake.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together.
Sift the next 5 ingredients together.
Combine the two mixtures and add the remaining ingredients one at a time.
Drop by large tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cajun fig cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and buttermilk and beat well.
Add remaining dry ingredients and stir carefully until all in.
Add figs, stirring well.
Bake almost 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Fry chicken to brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Mix sour cream with enough milk to thin.
Dip chicken in sour cream and milk.
Put in loaf pan and pour remainder of sour cream over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey-baked french toast
directions: In large bowl, beat milk, eggs, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons honey.
Dip bread into egg mixture, allowing both sides to absorb egg mixture.
Arrange bread, overlapping slices, in greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Pour any remaining egg mixture over bread.
(May be covered and refrigerated overnight at this point.) Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Drizzle with melted butter and 2 tablespoons honey.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Using palm of hand, flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg, then into crumbs to coat.
In skillet, over medium heat in butter, brown chicken on both sides.
Add Prego sauce.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: raspberry ripple cake
directions: Place raspberries and 1 tablespoon sugar in a food processor or blender and puree; set aside.
Combine margarine or butter and 1 1/4 cups sugar in mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Beat in egg whites and almond extract until smooth.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, oat bran and baking soda.
Add the flour mixture and the buttermilk to the margarine mixture.
Beat just until well mixed.
Remove 3/4 cup batter and mix with raspberry puree.
Set aside.
Coat a 12-cup Bundt pan with nonstick coating spray. Spread 2/3 batter evenly in pan.
Top with raspberry batter; follow with remaining plain batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before inverting on a wire rack.
Make glaze; transfer cake to serving platter and drizzle the glaze over the cake.
Makes 16 servings.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large iron skillet.
Cook on medium-low, stirring constantly, until mixture is crystallized, no liquid visible.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: springerle(german "picture cookies")
directions: Beat egg yolks and whites separately.
Then fold beaten yolks into whites.
Add butter and gradually add the sugar, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add soda and salt and stir 10 minutes more.
Add anise oil.
Gradually add flour to egg mixture.
Roll on floured board with rolling pin, about 1/8-inch thick.
Then roll with springerle rolling pin and cut around designs.
Place on towels and let stand overnight to set designs.
Bake following morning on lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Do not overbake or they will become hard.)
Store in container with tight-fitting lid.

title: apple-sausage ring
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly. Press lightly into a greased 6-cup ring mold. Turn out onto a shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Drain.

title: killer brownies
directions: Melt butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together; beat into cake mix.
Add almonds.
Put 1/2 of cake mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix well in a large casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sherry's stew
directions: Cook stew meat, mushroom soup, creamed corn, seasoning, onion and about 1/2 cup water overnight on low in crock-pot.
Cook potatoes and carrots separately.
Next morning, drain.
Add to crock-pot.
Heat on high for 30 minutes.
May add thickening if desired.
Serve with cornbread.

title: pasta with prosciutto and peas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add Prosciutto; saute over low heat. Add flour; cook for 3 minutes.
Slowly add cream; continue cooking until sauce thickens, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add peas, pepper, Parmesan, chives and parsley.
Bring to a simmer and keep warm.
Bring large pot of water to boil; add pasta.
Cook until tender.
Drain and toss with sauce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese and Colby cheese, Miracle Whip, Worcestershire and onion until blended together.
Form into ball. Nuts or parsley can be used to roll the cheese ball in.
Can be frozen or kept in the fridge for up to 2 weeks.
Flavor improves with age.

title: cheezy bars
directions: Spread one package of crescent rolls on greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread mixture on crescent rolls.
Spread other package of crescent rolls on top of mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, no longer.
Cool and refrigerate.
tags: amount of cinnamon and sugar mixed together

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until soft.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbled crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: zucchini hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in oiled (butter) oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cooled, cut into squares.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine all ingredients except for 1/2 of cheese, milk and crackers.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour on rest of milk; top with cheese and crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix butter, cocoa and flour until smooth.
Add sugar and milk. Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Bring to a boil in saucepan the shortening, margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar while still hot.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and nuts (optional).
Bake in a large sheet cake pan or two 8 x 1-inch cake pans for 20 minutes at 400°.
While cake is baking, make icing.

title: scalloped tuna and peas
directions: Place peas and tuna in layers in greased baking dish.
Add salt to cream and pour over fish.
Cover with crumbs and brown in moderate oven (350°).
Serves 6.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Pour sugar over apples in large bowl.
Let set for 30 minutes. Add oil and eggs; stir.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon bake
directions: Bake in loaf pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat undiluted tomato soup to boiling point.
Add gelatin. Melt cream cheese in soup; add shrimp, celery and onion.
Let cool 5 minutes and then add salad dressing.
Pour into a mold (slightly oiled) and refrigerate.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour over cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in freezer container and freeze.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery and onions.
In a separate bowl mix together mayonnaise, yogurt, mustard powder, sugar, pepper and celery seed.
Add vinegar and milk; stir until mixed.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour sauce over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer vegetables and season with salt and pepper.
Put hamburger on top.
Mix soup and water together.
Pour over casserole.
Cook on low heat 6 to 8 hours or high heat 2 to 4 hours.

title: barbecue pork and beef sandwiches
directions: About 8 1/2 hours before serving, in a 3 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker, combine all ingredients.
Cover and cook on high (300°) for 8 hours.
With wire whisk, stir mixture until meat is shredded.

title: versatile pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
While hot, place in a large container and drench with 3 cups Ranch dressing and 1/2 cup herb and spices.
Stir well. Cover and chill overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix sugar cookie mix as directed and bake on pizza pan.
Let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread over cookie. Top with bananas and strawberries.

title: crock-pot bean chowder
directions: Wash and drain lima beans.
Place in large crock-pot.
Add all the other ingredients; mix well.
Cook for 4 hours on high, then for 4 hours on medium.
Serve with cornbread.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine with marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sugar with sour cream or yogurt.
Stir into fruit.
Chill overnight.

title: no-bake cherry custard cake
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Press into 11 x 7 inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine pudding, milk and lite sour cream.
Beat until thickened, about 2 minutes. Spread over cake.
Spoon cherry pie filling evenly over top of cake.
Chill thoroughly.
Serves 12.
184 calories, 9 mg cholesterol, 3 g fat, 319 mg sodium and 4 g protein.

title: carolyn p. henderson's fried potatoes and squash
directions: Dice all ingredients and put in frypan.
Put just enough oil to fry ingredients.
Cook until tender and brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: no-fault kindergarten parents' recipe
directions: Sprinkle with a touch of temper and tears.
Fold in a love of music and art.
Stir gently and shape into a beautiful girl or boy.
Bake for five years or until ready for school.
Wrap and label carefully.
Send special delivery to Mrs. Selleck for polishing and safekeeping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Using the same beater, cream butter, then add sugar and syrup, creaming constantly.
Put eggs in while still mixing.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Make small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Put a Hershey's Kiss on after they come out of oven.
Put on cookie sheet in freezer until cool.

title: kenneth's cream cheese surprise
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix in 1/2 bottle of chutney or mint jelly.
Add onion, vinegar, lemon juice and a clove of garlic.
Mix all together and form into a ball or any shape desired.
Mix chopped pecans and olives together and place on top of cream cheese.
Serve with assorted crackers or wheat or pumpernickel bread.

title: easy tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in pan or microwave.
Mix all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Add coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Spread over filling.
Bake until peaks are golden brown.
Sprinkle top with coconut.
Cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in seasoned water until tender.
Debone and cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Do not use skin.
Strain the broth and use to cook spaghetti.
You may have to add water or canned chicken broth.
Melt margarine in skillet and saute vegetables until tender.
Add soup, pimiento and diced chicken; heat on warm temperature while spaghetti is cooking.
Drain cooked spaghetti; add to other mixture gently and last, add cheese.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add cold water; cook over medium heat until mixture is clear and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Add Jell-O, stirring until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.
Clean and slice strawberries.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Let set in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: mom's summer sausage
directions: Heat oven to 150°.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly on the first day.
Refrigerate.
Remix on second day.
Refrigerate. Remix on the third day.
Shape into 6 (4 to 5 ounce) rolls and refrigerate.
On the fourth day, place on cookie sheet and bake in a 150° oven for 4 hours and turn on other side.
Cook for another 4 hours.
Cool 2 to 3 hours then wrap individually into regular Reynolds Wrap.
Freeze to eat later or refrigerate to eat now. Serve cold slices as an appetizer or snack.

title: asparagus, brie and bacon muffins
directions: Whisk olive oil, basil, mustard and garlic together and set aside.

title: brown bread
directions: Soak raisins and soda in water overnight.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Grease three 1 pound coffee cans and fill half full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 30 minutes. Lay cans on sides to cool.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Miracle Whip and nuts and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Fold in Miracle Whip and nuts before serving.
Serves 12.

title: ratatouille
directions: In large pot, heat oil over moderate heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until onion is light brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally until vegetables are tender and some liquid remains.
Top with 1/2 cup of grated Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms soft ball in cold water. Take off stove; add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour into greased pan. Cool and wait until hardened.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add sugar and salt, beating until very stiff.
Fold in pecans.
Spread pecan mixture in prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until mixture is browned and all butter is absorbed, stirring at 10 minute intervals to coat evenly.
Remove to waxed paper while still warm; cool completely. Store pecans in an airtight container.
Yield: about 3 1/2 cups.

title: potato salad 2
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain them in a strainer to remove all the water.

The secret to keep your potatoes from becoming mushy is to let them sit until they are completely cool. After they have cooled add the eggs (be sure to mash the eggs up real good before you put them in).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and add about half the jar of pickle relish.
Then you add enough mayonnaise for it to mix up real well.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, sugar, vinegar and Miracle Whip.
Pour over macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and cut up in small chunks.
Saute onion. Combine Veg-All, onions, garlic, soup and milk.
Add chicken and pour into deep dish pie crust.
Cover with regular pie crust. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend sugar, butter and graham cracker crumbs together.
Press into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in butter over medium heat, no more than 10 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper and other spices.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line baking dish with 8 pieces of chipped beef.
Wrap 1 slice of bacon around each chicken breast and lay on top of chipped beef.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mushrooms rockefeller
directions: Lightly oil a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Clean mushrooms and dry.
Pull out stems.
Place bottoms in baking dish; set aside.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse and sort the beans.
Soak them overnight in 8 to 10 cups of cold water; do not change the water.
Bring the water to a soft boil.
As the water heats, mince the garlic and chop the celery, then saut them.
Add all with parsley, onion, bay leaves and seasonings to beans.
Cover and boil gently, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 hours.
It will thicken as the water reduces.
The last hour or so, you may wish to remove the lid.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and heat the juice.
Add jello and stir.
Melt marshmallows in heated juice.
Add fruit and fold in cream that has been whipped.
Add pecans to fruit and cream mixture. Refrigerate.
Serves 9.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and let set overnight. Mix the last 6 ingredients and blend well.
Pour over carrots and chill.

title: pastry hearts
directions: Cut margarine into flour as for pie crust.
Put the cottage cheese in the blender with the vanilla and blend until the mixture is like whipped cream.
Pour this mixture over the flour mixture and mix until all the flour is moistened with the cottage cheese. Place in the refrigerator overnight.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and Junket together.
Beat eggs to a fluff consistency.
Add milk and eggs; beat.
Add all other ingredients; beat again.
Add vanilla and enough milk to bring freezer to fill line.
Freeze in freezer.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Build up 1/2-inch edge.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Beat remaining ingredients 3 minutes.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake another 25 minutes or longer.
Cool and cut into squares.
Put powdered sugar on top.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Cut and peel the apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and pour over the apples. Melt butter. Add egg, flour and sugar.
Pour over the apples. Bake at 325° until brown, approximately 40 minutes.

title: aunt roz's slum gullion
directions: Dice potatoes, carrots and onions, then boil until tender in a small amount of water.
Braise beef in frypan; drain, then add cooked vegetables.
Simmer until heated through.
Season with salt, pepper and thyme.
Surprisingly good!

title: parmesan noodles
directions: Combine eggs and milk. Add Parmesan and enough of the flour to make a stiff dough.
(Add more flour, if necessary.)
Cover and let rest a few minutes.

title: shrimp superb
directions: Cut each shrimp in half lengthwise.
Cut each egg into eighths. In large bowl, combine the shrimp, egg sections, Blue cheese, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, honey and salt.
Mix very gently and slowly, until well blended.
Rub a 2-quart casserole with butter or margarine.
Turn the shrimp mixture into it, and sprinkle with 1 cup of finely crushed potato chips.
Bake in a preheated 250° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6. Rich and delicious.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread both slices of bread with mayonnaise.
Place corned beef, Swiss cheese and Havarti cheese on one slice of bread.
Top with sauerkraut and Thousand Island dressing.
Grill sandwich on both sides.
Serve with kosher pickle and chips of your choice.

title: mule ears
directions: Shape into rolls and refrigerate.
Slice and dip into sugar or form into balls and dip into cream and powdered sugar.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed.
Add flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Place in large tube pan and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: supper bake
directions: Place pieces of meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend water and flour.
Stir in gravy and cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in beans and onion.
Pour over meat.
Top with mounds of mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with chips or crackers.
May add onion, if desired.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 35 minutes at 350°.
(Recipe may be doubled.)

title: ham pork loaf
directions: Mix meat, milk, bread crumbs, eggs and mustard.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over loaf and bake another hour at 350°.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Peel cucumber, cut in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds.
Cut cucumber and onions into 1 inch pieces.
Place in blender.
Add soup and water.
Puree until smooth.
Add sour cream and pepper sauce.
Puree just to blend.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with cucumber slices.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cake internationale
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray two 9-inch round cake pans with Pam.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs until mixture is very light and fluffy.
Add extract.
Combine mixture alternately with sour cream.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Spread Wilderness cherry fruit filling on top.
Sprinkle Streusel topping over cherry fruit filling.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pecans) until it makes a firm roll.
Roll into ball, then dip or roll in pecans.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a saucepan. Add butter and milk. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Season washed and cut up chicken with salt, pepper, paprika and garlic salt, if desired.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix tomato paste and beer together.
Pour over chicken.
Add olives.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients, except tomato sauce; pack in a greased loaf pan.
Pour tomato sauce over top of meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: linguica hors d'oeuvres
directions: Grind together the linguica, onion and cheese using food grinder or food processor.
Cut crust off bread and quarter each slice.
Top each piece of bread with linguica mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 10 minutes or until top browns and cheese melts.

title: lemon filled cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this alternately with 1 cup milk.
Fold in 6 beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Blend together milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper.
Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
(The recipe plates are perfect.)
Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Heat broccoli (vegetable mixture) in this.
Spread broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in bottom of pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute by hand. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes depending on your oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.
Will freeze well also.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: company potatoes
directions: Chop onion and saute in butter until transparent.
Combine with frozen potatoes, sour cream, chicken soup and 1 cup of cheese.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and corn flakes on top.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chicken cheese meltaway
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse. Melt margarine; add onion.
Cook over low heat 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper.
Add milk gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Put 1/2 of macaroni in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 of chicken and cheese (in chunks).
Repeat layers.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered, and 5 minutes more uncovered.

title: pumpkin yummy
directions: Combine first seven ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture and drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: methodist punch
directions: Add sugar to hot tea, then add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Stir well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Fills one punch bowl.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch Pyrex dish, layer as follows:

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until they are cooked done enough to mash.
Drain.
Save approximately 1 1/2 cups of the potato water. Mix dry milk with water.
Use this, adding as you mash the potatoes, until they are fluffy.
Mix in cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Coat sheet cake pan with spray margarine.
Layer noodles, potatoes and onion.
Repeat layers.
Top with onion.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Mix all well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in greased skillet until brown.

title: strawberry meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Fold in crackers and pecans.
Spread in well-buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool. Fill with strawberries and top with whipped cream.

title: yogurt dill dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill until served.
Serve over tossed green salad.
Makes 1 cup.

title: light and lemon pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour in shell and chill.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain well.
Add spices, tomatoes, soup and rice.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in sliced olives.
Cover with shredded cheese. Cover and let stand until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: mom's party meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spoon into balls.
Brown in skillet; drain thoroughly.
Add tomato sauce and preserves.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with cracker and cheese on toothpicks.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Combine.
Pour over chicken; cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn chicken half way through and add can of mushrooms.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook as directed on package until tender.
Drain.
Saute onions in margarine.
Thoroughly mix onion and remaining ingredients with spaghetti in large bowl.
Put spaghetti mixture in 2 containers and freeze.
To serve, thaw and put in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven until bubbly, 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes a large amount.

title: banana cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375. Cream together butter & sugar. Add banana, egg & vanilla mix well. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon & allspice and add to mixture. Stir in nuts, raisins. Drop cookies on well greased cookie sheet. Bake 15-20 minutes.

title: crab-shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all together and put crumbs on top.
Grease baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dutch leek casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil and cook potatoes until tender but firm, about 15 minutes. Drain potatoes and transfer to a medium bowl.
Mash together with milk.
Place leeks in a medium saucepan with enough water to cover and bring to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
In a medium skillet over medium heat, cook and stir the ground beef until evenly brown.
Mix in the onion, red and green bell peppers.
Season with green chile peppers and soy sauce.
Continue to cook and stir until vegetables are tender.
In a medium baking dish, mix mashed potatoes, leeks and ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and top with ham.
Bake 25 minutes in preheated oven until bubbly and lightly browned. Serves 8.

title: orange cupcakes
directions: Put orange juice in medium size pan; add yeast and honey. Stir in 1 cup whole wheat flour and let stand in a warm place until bubbly, about 10 or 15 minutes.
Beat egg until foamy and then stir in oil, honey and 1 cup whole wheat flour, salt and vanilla.
When yeast is bubbly, stir it into egg mixture.
Fill cupcake papers or greased tins 1/2 full.
Turn oven to 150°.
Let cupcakes rise in oven 40 minutes until they almost reach top of pan.
Then turn oven to
350° and bake 20 minutes.
Cool and eat. Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine dip mix, dill weed, oil, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Pour over crackers and stir until well mixed.
Pour into jelly roll pan, spreading out evenly.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Nice to serve in small Dixie cups.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oil.
Form mixture into balls.
Heat oil and brown meat balls in oil.
Place meat balls into sauce and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Add the sifted sugar gradually and cream these ingredients well.
Stir
the flour mixture in 3 parts into the sugar mixture, alternating
with 1 can condensed tomato soup.
Stir the
batter until
smooth after each addition.	Fold in 1 cup nutmeats	and
1 cup raisins.
Bake in a greased tube or Bundt pan
at
for 45	minutes.
Spread, when cool with cream cheese frosting.

title: creates its own crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Precook broccoli for 10 minutes. Drain.
Add mayonnaise, cheese, soup, eggs and onions.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle extra cheese and saltine cracker crumbs on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: layered ground beef casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 of onions, celery and peppers.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with ground beef. Pour tomato sauce over.
Top with remaining onions, peppers and celery.
Salt and pepper.
Arrange potato slices on top.
Spread with soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Do not stir.

title: chili
directions: Mix cans of everything together.
Saute onions, then brown and drain meat.
Add to other stuff.
Add chili powder.
Add your peppers and heat up or let simmer for 1/2 or 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in iron skillet.
Add pineapple and cherries.
Mix eggs, sugar and fruit juice.
Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Recipe is from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: "ho...da good" sardines
directions: * More or less to suite your taste; mix together.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch dish.
Slice Twinkies in half longway.
Lay in dish with cream side up.
Pour thawed strawberries over.
Mix milk, pudding, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Pour over top. Chill and serve.
Excellent.

title: pizza mac
directions: Cook Creamettes until tender.
Place Creamettes on high lip cookie sheet.
Mix egg through noodles. Pour spaghetti sauce on noodles.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Slice up tomatoes and pepper in small pieces and place on top.
Add pepperoni slices and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheezy pizza dinner
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with a salad on hot bread.

title: double peanut butter cookies(serves 2 dozen)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in syrup and milk.
Shape into 2-inch roll and chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Shape into small balls and freeze on cookie sheet.
When frozen, store in Baggies.
Cook frozen at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot as appetizer.

title: chicken can can
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 1 hour.
Good way to use leftover chicken or turkey.

title: rich chocolate truffles
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan combine whipping cream and chocolate. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chocolate melts (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir until melted and creamy.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; boil to thicken.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole. Top with 2 cups crushed potato chips and 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 375` for 30 minutes.

title: savory beef stroganoff
directions: Toss beef, flour and garlic powder.
In a 2-quart casserole, microwave margarine with onion at High (full power) for 2 minutes. Stir in dry mix blended with water.
Microwave for 8 minutes or until sauce is thickened, stirring once.
Stir in sour cream. Serve over hot noodles.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Marinate chicken in soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch.
Chop all vegetables into bite size pieces.
Heat wok or large frying pan to 400°.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil and stir-fry vegetables for 3 minutes, then remove from wok.
Add 3 tablespoons of oil; add chicken and stir-fry until chicken is white.
Immediately add hoisin sauce; mix thoroughly.
Re-add vegetables to heat.
Add cashews.
Serve over rice.

title: easy no bake key lime pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and condensed milk together on low until blended. Gradually add in lime juice and continue to beat until well blended. Pour into pie shell and chill until firm enough to slice. Serve with whipped cream.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Strain the juice of crushed pineapple.
Mix flour and sugar and add well beaten eggs.
Add this to the juice and cook until thick.
Let cool well.
Add the pineapple and miniature marshmallows, cut up.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in bowl and place in refrigerator.

title: sorghum syrup sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, sorghum syrup and eggs and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix real good.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Make into balls the size of a walnut and roll in sugar.
Bake at 325°
for 7 minutes.
Be sure and grease cookie sheets well (real well).

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt the butter, cocoa, shortening and water.
Remove from heat; sift sugar and flour and mix.
In small bowl, beat eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix with chocolate and bake in a well-greased and floured cake pan at 400° for 20 minutes (batter will be thin).

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Add seasoning and water. Cook to thicken and let cool.
Before serving, add corn chips and dressing.

title: fruit glow punch
directions: In a large bowl combine concentrates and apple juice.
Stir in ginger ale.
Spoon sherbet into the bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: potato beef casserole
directions: Combine soup, water, parsley, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, onion and beef.
Pour into lightly greased covered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended. Blend in melted butter. Stir in Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels and walnuts. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes three 9-inch pies.

title: oven omelet
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place rhubarb in pan.
Sprinkle over with sugar, then sprinkle jello over.
Top with marshmallows.
Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Pour cake over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: noel fruit bars
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; gradually beat in powdered sugar.
Stir in melted margarine then add dry ingredients.
Fold into egg mixture with nuts and fruits.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer chicken and broccoli in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice together.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and Crisco or Spry.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well by hand.
Bake in slow oven, 325°, for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with graham crackers.
Prepare pudding by directions on box.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and remaining pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers.
Spread pie filling over top.
Chill overnight.
Great and simple!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery into very fine pieces.
Cook in butter over low heat until tender.
Cook spaghetti per package directions.
Mix soup, boned chicken, pepper, onion, celery and pimento with cooked spaghetti.
Put in oven baking dish and top with grated sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ginger cream cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg, molasses and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and let chill 1 hour.

title: mock cabbage roll casserole
directions: Take medium head of cabbage; cut into 2-inch pieces.
Parboil in salt water until tender; drain.
Cook meat.
Cook rice.
Saute onion and add parsley.
Mix together meat, rice, onion and parsley.
Grease deep casserole.
Put layer of cabbage, then layer of meat, just enough to cover cabbage.
Continue to layer until all ingredients are used.
Pour tomato sauce or soup (diluted with 1/2 can water) over entire casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichokes and chop.
Combine with cheese, mayonnaise and garlic.
Place in 1/2-quart ovenproof baking dish and bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
Mixture may be prepared the night before and refrigerated until ready for baking.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. (Reserve some dough to go on top.)
Melt and mix together the next 4 ingredients on low heat until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat. Add rest of ingredients. Spread chocolate mixture over dough in pan. Crumble remaining dough on top and press lightly.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brilliant candy slices
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in pecans and cherries. Divide into rolls 10 inches long.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Cut into slices.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes, just brown at the edges.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: In skillet, brown and drain sausage.
Melt cheese and combine with sausage.
Add tomatoes and chillies.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt in double boiler: the peanut butter and margarine.
Mix in a large bowl: the Rice Krispies and powdered sugar.
Add melted mixture to cereal mixture.
Blend with hands until crumbly.
Make into small balls (approximately 9 dozen).
Set aside.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Makes 2 small loaves or bake in 9-inch square pan or a little larger at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add baking powder.
Alternately add milk and flour, ending with flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Stir jello in boiling water. Add softened cream cheese. May use mixer to blend well. Add pineapple and Coca-Cola. Mix well and chill for several hours.

title: sandy's punch
directions: Mix together juices and water.
Add just before serving time 2 quarts chilled ginger ale and 1 quart chilled soda water.
Makes enough to fill a large punch bowl.

title: grilled italian tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half crosswise and sprinkle each half with 1 teaspoon Italian dressing, 1/4 teaspoon basil, salt and pepper. Combine butter and breadcrumbs; spoon over tomato halves.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pan.
Bring to a boil. Remove cloves and then serve.

title: lemon basil soup with rice
directions: Combine broth and basil in a 3 quart saucepan.
Heat to a boil and stir in rice.
Reduce heat to simmer and cover.
Allow to simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
In a small bowl, combine lightly beaten egg yolks and lemon juice.
Beat with a fork until well mixed.
Temper the egg yolks by gradually adding about 1/4 cup of hot soup to the yolk/lemon juice mixture, beating with fork to blend.
Stir the tempered yolk mixture into the soup pot.
Cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until soup begins to thicken slightly.
Stir in butter.
Taste and add salt and black pepper, if needed.

title: thelma's corn casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the cheese.
Place in a casserole and bake uncovered for 10 minutes at 375°.
Place cheese on top and continue to cook for 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: cinnamon pancakes
directions: Combine flour, egg, oil and milk.
Add cinnamon and stir well. In hot buttered medium-high skillet, pour just enough batter for 1 pancake.
When edges are bubbled through, flip over.
Cover with butter and syrup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese; add pineapple and 1 cup pecans.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put mixture in a round bowl and chill. Form into a ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Soak
beans in water overnight.
Cook
slowly
in
same water until skins break.	Add salt,
brown
sugar,
molasses, mustard, Worcestershire
sauce, onion and catsup.
Put
beans into bean pot.
Wash salt pork; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Press into top of beans, leaving only rind exposed.
Cover
and bake at 275° for 6 to 8 hours, adding water
as necessary.
Uncover during the last 30 minutes to brown.
Serves 6.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Boil chicken breasts; remove meat from bone.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix rice, soups, milk and chicken. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: szechuan shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Peel and devein shrimp; cut in half lengthwise.
Rinse; pat dry with paper towels.
Set aside.

title: mother's date pudding
directions: *I do not use pre-cut dates.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together very well.
Form mixture into loaf.
Spread top of loaf with ketchup.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients into a saucepan; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let harden.

title: winning combination salad
directions: Cut broccoli, including tender part of stems, into bite size pieces and place in mixing bowl.
Add kidney beans, onion, raisins and bacon.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; make a hole in center.
Bring salt, oleo, Crisco, lard or oil, cocoa and water to boil and pour in well of flour and sugar.
Then add eggs, soda and buttermilk. Mix, beat and pour in cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cry babies(soft cookie)
directions: Mix together sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses. Alternately add water and dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes. While still warm, frost with a thick frosting made of powdered sugar, vanilla and milk or water.

title: "peach salad"
directions: Bring jello and crushed pineapple to boil over medium heat. Set aside and let cool.
Add buttermilk and fold in Cool Whip. Put in oblong dish and refrigerate.
Delicious.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter well.
Gradually add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; mix well. Pinch off small amount of dough and roll with hands into finger shapes or balls.

title: filling brownies
directions: Cream together the butter and cream cheese.
Add the sugar to this mixture; beat until fluffy.
Combine the eggs, flour and vanilla; blend into cream cheese mixture.
Spread 1/2 brownie mixture in pan.
Top with cheese mixture, then rest of brownie mixture.
Swirl just a little.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to box.
Add Cool Whip and mix until blended.
Layer graham crackers in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Pour half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Put one more layer of graham crackers and pour rest of pudding mixture on top.
Put top layer of graham crackers on and frost with chocolate frosting. Refrigerate overnight.

title: one-hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Milk, sugar, salt and butter should be put into pan over the oven and heated to lukewarm. Add yeast and flour and stir until blended. Put in a warm place for 15 minutes. Turn out on a floured board and press to inch thickness. Cut out circles. Fold dough over bits of butter. Place on greased cookie sheet. Let rise 15 minutes and bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Soak tortillas in chicken broth until soft.
Line 12 x 9-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Spoon small amount of broth over them.
Cover with pieces of chicken.
Mix soups together and pour over chicken.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic salt and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cover with grated cheese and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar-free popsicles
directions: Sprinkle gelatine on top of cold water and let dissolve.
Put Kool-Aid in boiling water and dissolve.
Pour cold mixture into hot mixture and stir.
Divide mixture into ice pop trays.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons of melted margarine in microwave a minute at a time until melted.
Spread over first mixture (fridge for 15 minutes).
Then put back in fridge until firm.
Very important:
Cut squares on time and return to fridge.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and marshmallows in cream and cherry juice. Add 1/2 cup sugar extra.

title: easy italian meatballs
directions: Meat must be fresh or used immediately once defrosted. Combine all ingredients really well with very clean hands.
Form into meatballs of your desired size.
Heat electric skillet to medium heat.
Add a tablespoon of olive oil and rotate to spread oil over pan bottom.
Place meatballs in skillet and brown slowly on all sides.
Once browned, reduce heat, cover and cook through, about 20 minutes more.
Serve with traditional tomato sauce over spaghetti.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together.
Use heaping 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup and add hot water.

title: ruth's noodles
directions: Bring noodles to a boil.
Drain.
Add butter to noodles.
Pour enough noodles into deep baking pan to cover bottom.
Pour a layer of milk gravy over noodles to cover.
Put a layer of cheese.
Put another layer of milk gravy over noodles and and a top layer of cheese.
Serve while hot.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Arrange artichoke hearts in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cook onion in butter in large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly until tender.
Stir in spinach, sour cream and the next 4 ingredients.
Spoon mixture over artichokes; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serves 8.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing together and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle cashews over top of this, then add bacon bits.
Let salad set in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Wash flower pot.
Place whipped topping lid in bottom.
Put cookies in blender.
Make fine crumbs resembling dirt.
Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar in small bowl; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Now add cream cheese mixture to the pudding.
Place cookie crumbs in pot 1/2-inch thick.
Alternate cookie crumbs and cream mixture until pot is full.
Finish with 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Chill for 6 hours.
Garnish with silk flowers or greenery.
Serve with trowel.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meats.
Soak breadcrumbs in milk for 5 minutes.
Add meats, eggs, onions, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/4 teaspoon dill weed, allspice, nutmeg and cardamom.
Mix well and refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.

title: summer squash
directions: Pour squash slices into boiling water.
Cook 2 minutes and drain.
Mix squash, chestnuts, soup, sour cream, onion and carrot together.
Pour in 1 large or 2 small casserole dishes.
Brown the cracker crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over squash mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Using pastry blender or two knives, cut in the Crisco.
Mix water, egg and vinegar, beating slightly with a fork; add to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until dough forms a ball.
Divide into four equal portions; wrap in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator to chill before rolling out.
Makes 2 double crusts.

title: monroe asparagus
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar, cloves, cinnamon stick, celery seed and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cool.
Pour over canned asparagus and cover.
Chill 12 hours or more.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine strawberries and 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Mix and let stand.
Mix dry ingredients; add oleo, eggs and strawberry mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip, then nuts.
Pour into loaf pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, pickles and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pack into green peppers from which seeds have been removed.
Chill, then cut in thick slices and serve on lettuce with segments of tomatoes, dipped in French dressing and whole ripe olives.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in an ungreased, large casserole.
Toss well. Heat bouillon in a saucepan with oil, garlic, bay leaf, salt, dill and savory.
Bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Yields 12 servings.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add next four ingredients.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Fry on heated griddle at 350° to 400°.

title: peach, strawberry or blueberry pie(diabetic, low-fat recipe)
directions: Bring to a boil, water; add cornstarch, then add jello.
Stir until cool.
Add fruit.
Put into baked pie shell.
Cool and add Cool Whip topping.
You can also use graham cracker shell.
Use light Cool Whip.

title: chicken salad spread
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on bread.
Yields 4 sandwiches.

title: baked pork chops and potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onion; dot with butter or margarine.
Mix flour, salt and pepper (to taste) and water together; pour over layers.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake until pork chops brown, turn once.

title: yankee beef tips
directions: Mix cubed roast, garlic salt, season salt and flour in a large bowl.
Stir together until all meat is well coated.
Place meat into large preheated frying pan with small amount of vegetable oil.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned.
Stir in 2 cans of beef broth and stir in 2 cans of warm water.
Cook until broth and water become gravy.
Serve over mashed potatoes or cooked rice.

title: hearty meat sauce
directions: About
minutes
before serving:
In 4 quart skillet over medium-high
heat,	cook
ground
beef, onion and garlic until pan juices evaporate and meat is well browned, stirring often. Add
tomatoes with their liquid and remaining ingredients, stirring to mix well
and
break
up
tomatoes over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce
heat
to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until done.
Mash with sugar and butter. Refrigerate 2 days.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Combine molasses, corn syrup, sugar, water and vinegar.
Cook to hard boil and reduce heat.
Then add butter.
Continue to cook until hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Wipe crystals off pan. Add baking soda.
Stir to mix thoroughly.

title: friday's super casserole(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until onion is transparent.
Add soup and milk and blend.
Combine remaining ingredients except buttered crumbs and turn into buttered casserole or baking dish.
Top with crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and lightly browned on top.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
