Add remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out dough thick and use plenty of flour.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all well and pour into 9x13 baking dish.
Bake 40 min. or until done at 375.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: waffle baked cookies
directions: Combine oleo and cocoa in saucepan; melt on stove and cool. Whip eggs and sugar with fork; add flour and cocoa mixture slowly. Add vanilla.
Heat waffle iron to medium.
Put 1 teaspoon butter in each part of iron.
Bake for 1 minute.
Let cool.

title: special blueberry muffins
directions: Cream vegetable shortening with the sugar.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Add the milk and mix well again.
Sift into the first mixture the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix by hand.
Fold in the blueberries very gently.
Fill muffin tins to the top. Sprinkle each muffin with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no knead crusty french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with sugar.
Let set 10 minutes until it foams.
In a bowl blend margarine with milk, flour and salt. Add yeast mixture and blend with a wooden spoon.
Gradually stir in 4 to 5 cups flour until smooth.
Oil a glass bowl and place dough in.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled by poking dough with finger.
If hole remains, dough has risen enough.
Punch down and divide into 2 pieces.
Form 2 long loaves in French bread pan or cookie sheet.
Slash dough in several diagonal lines.
Cover and let rise until doubled (test).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray loaves with warm water.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Drain beans.
Put 1 can of beans in the bottom of a greased casserole.
Combine sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle half of mixture, chopped bacon and ketchup over beans.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in slow (325°) oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: light rolls
directions: Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir to dissolve.
Stir in sugar, half of flour and salt.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add egg, the shortening and the rest of the flour.
Beat again.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 30 minutes).
Stir down and spoon into large muffin pan (which has been greased), filling each muffin cup about 1/2 full.
Let rise to top of pan (20 to 30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
While still warm, brush top with melted butter.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice the cucumbers and place in a large bowl, shaking salt over each layer of cucumbers.
Add onion.
Mix together sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad.
Stir.
Chill and serve.

title: frankly savory cabbage
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven or large deep skillet.
Add caraway seed and onion; saute until onion is tender.
Add cabbage; cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Sprinkle flour and salt over cabbage; stir to blend well.
Mix mustard into milk; gradually add to cabbage. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Cut frankfurters into 1-inch pieces.
Add to cabbage; simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until frankfurters are heated through.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Combine water, shortening, egg, lemon peel and juice.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack. Refrigerate and use as desired.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt margarine and butter in small saucepan with sugar.
Stir and boil for 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Break apart graham crackers and put in well-greased cookie sheet with 1-inch sides. Pour hot mixture over crackers. Spread.
Sprinkle sliced almonds over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 11 to 12 minutes.
Get out fast and put on waxed paper.
Separate and run knife under crackers. Store in tin.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in shortening.
Add meat and brown slightly, stirring.
Stir in flour, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Break up noodles and lightly brown in butter.
Add rice and salt; stir thoroughly.
Add chicken broth and bring mixture to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In skillet, melt butter. Add milk, then add all dry ingredients together. Stir with whisk.
Cook over medium heat until desired thickness.
Serve over biscuits.

title: beehive-oven apricot bread
directions: Cut dried apricots into pieces with scissors.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs, apricots and water in which apricots were soaked.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and blend into batter.
Add nuts.
Pour into 8 x 5 x 3-inch or 2 small buttered bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until the bread tests done.

title: raisin bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Heat milk, add to sugar, oleo, and salt.
Stir in yeast.
Mix in flour.
If too soft, add more flour.
Mix in raisins.
Knead.
Let rise about 1 1/2 - 2 hours.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Cut part of stems off of broccoli.
Peel skins off of stems left on, and cut into flowerets.
Wash very good.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, onion flakes and salt together thoroughly. Add oil and mix well.
Place broccoli in large Tupperware bowl with cover.
Cover with dressing.
Seal well and turn bowl over. Store upside down in refrigerator.
Turn bowl often.
This can be made a day or two ahead of time.
Note:
You can add slivered carrots to the broccoli to add color.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Break up soaked bread and mix with egg, hamburg, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in flour and brown in oil.
Drain and add water, sugar, salt, tomato sauce, white vinegar, pickle relish, pineapple chunks, green peppers and carrot.
Cook until liquid cooks down to 2/3.
May be cooked in electric skillet and later put in casserole.

title: brown betty
directions: Mix together 3/4 cup sugar, lard, salt, soda, flour and oats. Put 1/2 of it in pan.
Then put apples and raisins on top of mixture.
Put 3/4 cup sugar evenly over apples.
Then put rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 375°.

title: deviled corn custard
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg yolks; mix in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add butter and allow to melt. Add corn, ham, mustard and seasonings.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into corn mixture.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole one hour or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken in 1 quart water.
When done, strain stock and add tomatoes, lean pork (diced), lean beef, the cut up chicken, onions, tomatoes, bacon grease and V-8.
Cook 3 hours.
Add potatoes and lima beans and cook for 1 hour, then add sugar, corn, bay leaves, oregano, Worcestershire and salt and pepper.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In a medium pan, place cornstarch.
Slowly stir in the chicken broth.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until slightly thick. Slowly add egg and stir once gently.
Remove from heat.
Garnish with green onions and serve at once.

title: angel hair pasta with scallops and shrimp
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine and oil. Add garlic; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add reserve shrimp liquid, wine, oregano and red pepper.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat.
Boil until liquid is reduced slightly, about 5 minutes.
Add scallops and cook until scallops turn opaque.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Add parsley and shrimp to sauce.
Toss hot pasta with sauce.
Garnish with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; stir in eggs, syrup, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Bake on lower oven rack in preheated 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple-raisin waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple pieces.
Reserve the juice to soak the diced apples to prevent discoloration.
Plump raisins in hot water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well and place all of the items on paper towels to insure dryness.

title: baked apple
directions: Pare apple halfway down and place in shallow casserole.
Add water, lemon juice and vanilla.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon. Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese and whipped topping.
Layer cherries and topping mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Mix ingredients all together and then refrigerate for at least an hour.
Shape into crescent shape using floured hands.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Into a large bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, beat the eggs.
Add oil and buttermilk and mix well.
Make a deep well in the dry ingredients and pour liquid mix in.
Stir by hand, just enough to moisten dry mix.
Fold in the Raisin Bran cereal.

title: original kentucky whiskey cake
directions: Soak cherries and raisins or dates in bourbon overnight. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well. Add soaked fruit and remaining liquid and the flour (reserving a small amount of nuts); add to butter-egg yolk mixture.
Add nutmeg and baking powder.
Fold into beaten egg whites.
Add lightly floured nuts last.
Bake in a large greased tube pan lined with greased paper for 3 to 4 hours in a slow 250° or 275° oven.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces with diced vegetables.
Start with bacon, layer vegetables in large soup pot.
Cover and steam 20 minutes. Add clams, clam
juice, tomatoes and cold water.
Season with thyme and parsley to cover vegetables and sprinkle with garlic salt, pepper and salt. Simmer for 2 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: blueberry grape salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add pie filling and crushed pineapple with juice and mix. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill. Blend cream cheese, sour cream and sugar together well. Spread over set salad. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of cream cheese layer.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Blend together all ingredients. Roll into small balls and drop on an ungreased cookie sheet. Press down flat with finger. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar (optional) and bake at 325° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 8 dozen small cookies.

title: roast turkey with herb rub
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Pat turkey dry with paper towels and place on rack set in large roasting pan.
If not stuffing turkey, place herb sprigs in main cavity.
If stuffing turkey, spoon stuffing into main cavity.
Tie legs together loosely to hold shape of turkey.
Brush turkey with oil.
Rub herb mix all over turkey.
Place turkey neck and giblets in roasting pan.
Position rack in lowest third of oven and preheat to 425°.
Drizzle melted butter all over turkey.
Pour 2 cups broth into pan.
Roast turkey 45 minutes.
Remove turkey from oven and cover breast with foil.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Return turkey to oven.
Roast unstuffed turkey 1 hour (stuffed turkey 1 hour and 30 minutes).
Remove foil from turkey; pour remaining 2 cups broth into roasting pan.
Continue roasting until turkey is done, basting occasionally with pan juices (about 1 hour and 40 minutes longer).

title: crock-pot pork chop casserole
directions: Place ingredients in a 2-quart crock-pot in layers as listed. Cook on high for about 8 hours.

title: working girl's favorite(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients, except biscuits or waffles, in lightly oiled crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 6 to 10 hours.
Serve spooned over hot biscuits. Makes 2 quarts.

title: magic milkshake
directions: In a blender put cold water; add powdered milk, sugar and vanilla.
Begin to blend adding the ice cubes one at a time until the machine stops making horrible noises and the shake is thick and smooth.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Bake 2 regular 9-inch pie crusts and cool.
Cook other ingredients on top of stove until thick and pour into already baked pie shells.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and slice or cube potatoes; boil until tender.
Drain well.
Cream the potatoes, margarine, salt, pepper and grated onion (including juice) together, using enough milk to make it creamy.
Stir in cheese; put in a casserole dish.
Heat at 325° for approximately 20 minutes, or until mixture is completely hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger in pan and drain grease off.
Add tomatoes, onions and chilies and simmer 20 minutes.
Layer in individual bowls, lettuce, Fritos and cheese, then top with hamburger sauce. This can be topped with tomato cubes, fresh onions and mild or hot taco sauce.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows and stir.
Separate cream cheese as you are stirring. Add pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate until it sets.

title: easy chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine, peanut butter and vanilla.
Remove from stove.
Add confectioners sugar and cocoa; mixing thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch square baking pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: pork chops and noodles
directions: Cook noodles a few minutes in boiling, salted water.
Drain, rinse well in cold water.
Grease large baking dish.
Put in noodles, celery, onions, pimentos, cayenne, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cans tomato soup.
Mix well with fork.
Pour off excess grease from pork chops and place chops over noodles mixture.
Cover with remaining 1/2 can tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning chops often.

title: old-fashioned taffy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and cream of tartar in a saucepan; stir until boiling begins.
Continue boiling until mixture forms a ball when dropped into a small bowl of very cold water.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered platters.
When cool enough, pull with buttered hands. Add coloring while pulling.
When candy is light in color and gets hard to pull, cut in fourths.
Pull each piece into long strand, about 1/2 inch thick with buttered scissors.
Quickly snip in bite-size pieces.
Wrap each in waxed paper.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: cranberry supreme
directions: *May substitute raspberries or blueberries for cranberries.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening with hot water.
Add cold water and yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and flour.
Let stand until dough has risen double.
Work down.
Make into rolls; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix oil and chips in microwave and melt together.
Pour over Crispix and stir.
Put powdered sugar in a Ziploc bag, put cereal in and shake.
A great snack food.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Thaw shrimp.
Cut large shrimp in half.
Melt shortening; blend in flour and brown, stirring constantly.
Add water gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove bay leaves.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: scandinavian peach pudding
directions: Drain peaches thoroughly.
In mixing bowl, sift together stirred flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Beat egg until thick and add to dry ingredients with drained peaches.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Turn into ungreased baking dish (sheet cake size).

title: mom's applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Blend in applesauce and lemon juice.
Pour into individual molds or a serving dish. Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or 5 to 7 servings.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix 1 egg and cake mix.
Stir in melted butter.
Press mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Beat 3 eggs, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Pour on top of cake mix mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: zesty stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray or grease lightly.
Cook zucchini 5 minutes in boiling salted water; drain.
Cut lengthwise slice from each to within 1 inch of ends.
Scoop out pulp and chop with slices. Combine pulp, stuffing, cheese and pepper.
Stuff into shells, mounding on top.
Dot with butter.
Place in dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or freeze until ready to cook.

title: nana's taco dip
directions: Microwave potato; peel and mash.
While warm, mix with taco seasoning, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
In shallow dish, layer bean dip, potato mix, vegetables and Cheddar cheese. Serve with plain, unseasoned chips.
I use a pedestal type dish and arrange vegetables in an attractive manner.
Leftovers keep well covered and refrigerated.
Serves 15.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place rice and soup mix in the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt chicken lightly and put in a single layer on top of rice.
Mix chicken soup with water.
Pour over all and bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Cover with foil and uncover the last 1/2 hour to brown slightly.
More water may be added, if needed.

title: miracle fruit cake
directions: Make up spice cake mix according to package directions, adding 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
If desired, up to 1 tablespoon sherry, rum or brandy may be added.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese. Add milk and continue beating until smooth.
Mix in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours. Top
with cherries.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Layer tortillas with cheese, chicken and onions.
Top with soups, broth and chilies.
Grate more cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Crumble sausage and cook; drain well.
Mix cheese and sausage. Sprinkle in pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour over sausage mixture in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: roasted garlic lime chicken
directions: Spray 13 X 9 X 2 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray; arrange chicken in dish.
Sprinkle chicken with lime juice, then garlic salt and seasoned pepper.
Roast in 400 degree oven until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear when cut, about 30 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: In a 3 1/2 or 4-quart crock-pot, combine undrained pineapple, dried fruit, sugar and rum or whiskey.
Stir in orange peel, lemon peel, orange and lemon juice.
Cover; cook on low heat for 9 to 10 hours or on high heat for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
To serve, gently stir in drained cherries.
Cover; cook on low or high heat for 15 minutes more.
Serve warm over slices of pound cake or ice cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serves 100.

title: cabbage-sausage dinner
directions: Cut sausage into serving size pieces.
Grill in Dutch oven or large skillet over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add potatoes, onion, carrots, green pepper and cabbage in layers.
Add water, salt or pepper as desired.
Cover and allow to steam until vegetables attain desired degree of tenderness.

title: party chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan; top each with cheese slice.
Sprinkle on mushrooms.
Mix soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Lightly crumble stuffing; sprinkle over chicken.
Dribble butter over the stuffing and chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Melt all in double boiler.
Serve warm.
Keep in refrigerator. Reheat in double boiler.

title: sunny silver pie
directions: Cook yolks in 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and rind of lemon over water in double boiler.
Beat with beater until creamy. (Note:
When cooking egg yolk mixture over double boiler, stir frequently and cook to pudding thickness.)
Then take off stove and beat in gelatin.
Let it set in hot water while beating egg whites, other 1/2 cup sugar and pinch of salt.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold into egg mixture.
Place in baked shell. Chill overnight.

title: chili burger supper
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until done; drain thoroughly. Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Add soups and macaroni; stir well.
Pour into casserole dish; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Halve the cheese slices diagonally. Remove foil and place cheese on meat mixture.
Return to the oven for about 1 or 2 minutes. Serve hot.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt
the
margarine and stir in the brown sugar, syrup and salt. Bring to
a
boil, stirring constantly; boil without stirring 5 minutes. Remove	from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over the popcorn. Mix well. Turn into 2 large shallow baking
dishes.
Bake in 250° oven 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.	Remove from oven; cool completely. Break apart and
store
in	tightly
covered container.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Can serve or garnish with ice cream.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish with 2 teaspoons water. Cover and microwave for 6 to 7 minutes, until tender; drain. Arrange chicken in bottom of square microwave pan.
Place broccoli on top and cover with cheese.
In a mixing bowl, combine milk, Worcestershire sauce, nutmeg and soup.
Blend together and pour on top of the broccoli and chicken mixture.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add broccoli and mix well. Add remaining ingredients, breaking the cheese slices into small pieces. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes (preheat oven).

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Combine baking mix, sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in pie filling, milk, egg, melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into a greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes in tube pan.

title: quick honey gingerbread
directions: Grease 19 cm x 29 cm baking pan; line base with paper and grease paper.
Combine flours, soda, spices and sugar in processor; process a few seconds until combined.
Combine honey, water and butter in saucepan; stir over low heat until butter is melted.
Add to processor; process until mixture is smooth.
Pour into prepared pan and bake in moderate oven for about 35 minutes.
Dust with sifted icing sugar before serving.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Cut chicken into halves (8 halves).
Roll dry beef and chicken together, then wrap bacon around both.
Put into baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Pour over top of chicken. Cover and bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: hot dog salad
directions: Grind up hot dogs, pickles and eggs.
Mix well; set aside.
Mix dressing and mustard together, use pickle juice.
Mix altogether.

title: chocolate dipped peanut butter balls(makes about 6 dozen)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together; slowly add peanut butter and Rice Krispies crumbs and cream all together.
Roll into small balls (about 1-inch in diameter).
Before rolling into balls: Melt in a double boiler, Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Hershey bar should be broken into small pieces and the paraffin wax should be cut into small pieces.
After chocolate and wax mixture is melted, dip balls in the chocolate mixture and put on waxed paper or foil to cool.
Keep chocolate mixture warm while dipping.
(I use 2 forks to place balls into and remove from mixture.)
Just place balls into mixture; roll them around and remove promptly.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour half of mix in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt caramels in the milk and pour over the cake in pan.
Sprinkle chips over caramel, then add pecans. Pour rest of cake mix over pecans and bake 25 minutes or until done at 350°.
Put your favorite icing on the cake.
I like to put caramel icing on mine.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients; bake about 30 minutes or until light brown on top.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Cover with 2 1/2 cups water.
Boil 10 minutes and drain.
Put in Tupperware container with tight lid.
Boil sugar, oil and vinegar for 10 minutes.
Pour over kraut mixture. Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat.
Add mushrooms.
Stir soup and flour into water with whisk and heat.
Stir until thickened.
Combine with meat. Serve over cooked noodles with a dollop of yogurt.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: Melt sugar and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Mix in other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator in plastic container.
Will keep all winter in fridge.

title: short cut homemade soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add to large Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients and cook on low for 1 hour.
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: holiday rainbow cake
directions: Crush half the cookies (about 20) to make crumbs. Combine crumbs with melted margarine and press into the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan or pie plate. Stand remaining cookies around edge of pan. Spread 3/4 cup fudge topping over crust. Freeze 15 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix egg, sugar, milk and shortening. Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well and pour into waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan. Sprinkle with mixture of
the brown sugar, cinnamon, flour and melted butter (optional 1/2 cup nuts). Spread over dough. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add dry pudding, mix. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 c. pudding into bowl, layer cookies then bananas.
Repeat: ending with pudding. Refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Then alternate with milk and flour mixture.
After well blended, add bananas and nuts. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until golden brown. Toothpick test will not work for doneness.

title: pork chop rice casserole
directions: Put chops in a casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chops and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick pizza dough
directions: Put flours and baking powder into a large bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add butter and margarine and rub in with fingertips until mixture resembles bread crumbs. Stir in enough milk to form a dough. Turn onto a lightly floured surface; knead briefly.
Roll out dough to a 10-inch circle. Transfer to a greased baking sheet.
Use as directed in recipe.

title: shrimp-mushroom-artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter and saut mushrooms.
Place in 2-quart casserole, one layer each of artichokes, shrimp and mushrooms.
Melt butter; add flour, stirring with wire whisk, then add milk and cream. Stir and cook until thickened.
Add sherry, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix in crabmeat.	Pour sauce over layered ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then paprika.	Serve over rice.

title: chicken and bacon dish
directions: Wrap the chicken in one piece of bacon. Mix together the golden cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and milk. Pour over chicken breasts. Bake at 300° for 2 hours, covered, or 1 hour, uncovered.

title: sangria
directions: Simmer cinnamon sticks, sugar and a dash of regular cinnamon in 2 cups of wine for about 10 minutes.
In large bowl put simmered mixture, and 2/3 of the 2 liter bottle of diet pop. Slice fruit and add to the bowl.
Chill for at least 2 hours. Remove cinnamon sticks and serve.

title: dancers delight(ants on a log)
directions: Clean celery and cut into 3 or 4-inch pieces.
Spread peanut butter in hollow of celery.
Sprinkle with raisins.

title: chicken or turkey noodle bake
directions: Blend milk into soup.
Stir in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except melted butter or margarine and crackers.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter; place on top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Mix together (uncooked) and spread on cocktail rye bread slices.
Top with Ragu (or other prepared spaghetti sauce), Mozzarella cheese and garlic salt.
Broil until cheese melts and is nicely browned.

title: quick chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions; set aside.
Mix in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan the sugar, cocoa, water and marshmallows.
Now spoon mixed batter over the mixture in pan. Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Excellent served warm topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: scones
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and raisins.
Cut in oleo; in a separate bowl, mix milk and eggs.
Add wet ingredients to dry and lightly knead together.
Form a circle; cut part way through into 8 pieces.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°; serve warm or cold.
"Warm" best; serve with butter and jam.

title: warm bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble.
Mix egg, vinegar and sugar.
In a saucepan, heat mixture, stirring constantly to keep egg smooth.
Heat until mixture boils and slightly thickens. Add crumbled bacon or Bac*Os.
Pour lightly over lettuce or raw spinach for a delicious salad.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then top with cornflakes (1 cup) and dot with margarine and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Let cheese soften and then mix with marshmallow cream and pineapple juice until smooth and creamy.
Serve with your choice of fresh fruit cut into bite sized pieces.

title: pita bread
directions: Mix water and margarine into bowl until margarine is melted. Sprinkle with yeast packet from roll mix.
Stir.
Add flour mixture; blend well.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface for 2 minutes.
Cover; let rise until double, 30 to 45 minutes.
Lightly sprinkle corn meal on 2 ungreased cookie sheets.
Divide dough into 6 equal pieces.
Shape into balls.
Roll out each one into a 7-inch circle.
Place 3 on each sheet.
Let rise 30 minutes. (For sesame seed bread, brush with milk and sprinkle seed.)
Bake at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cut crosswise to make pockets.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have a 13 x 9-inch baking dish ready.
In a medium size bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, tofu, all but 2 tablespoons Parmesan, egg whites, salt and pepper until blended. Spread 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Cover sauce with a layer of cooked and drained lasagna noodles.
Spread 1/2 of the Ricotta mixture over noodles, then half the spinach, shredded Mozzarella and sauce.
Continue layering as follows: more noodles, remaining Ricotta mixture, spinach and Mozzarella, remaining noodles and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with reserved Parmesan and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 1 hour, or until bubbly around edges.
Serves 6.

title: christmas popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add marshmallows.
Stir over medium heat until melted. Add dry gelatin and stir.
Pour hot mixture over popcorn.

title: pudding pops
directions: Pour milk into bowl and add pudding.
Mix with beater.
Take spoon and gently stir in whipped topping.
Pour in popsicle containers.
Put in freezer overnight or until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients
except
potato chips.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top
with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: *If use
all plain flour, add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Cook potatoes until tender (cut them up like making potato salad).
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into baking dish.
Combine butter and cereal crumbs.
Mix until evenly coated.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 50 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover and slit.
Brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1/2 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Beat milk and peanut butter.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Mix well.
Make 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Squish Kisses on top when removed from oven.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown together ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain thoroughly and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and simmer for 10 minutes or more.
Best if made a day ahead.	Serves 16.

title: easy crab imperial
directions: In medium sized pan, melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, to keep mixture smooth.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil and thickens, stirring frequently.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes. Cool and fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another pan heat margarine until lightly browned.
Add crab and toss lightly.
Combine with sauce mixture.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Melt together chocolate and butter.
Slowly add sugar (1/2 cup at a time) and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Bring to a rapid boil until glossy.
Cool 2 minutes.
Add salt and vanilla.

title: chili con queso
directions: We serve this dish as a hot appetizer.
It often becomes the main course, though, when we can't stop eating!

title: queso dip
directions: Brown meat and drain. Melt cheese over low heat. When smooth, add other ingredients. Mix and heat. Serve with chips.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with 1/2 pound of crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° until cake springs back when pressed with finger.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add egg, vanilla and milk. Mix in part of sugar and chocolate, then butter and rest of sugar. Place in a greased pan and chill.
Nuts may be added.

title: spoon biscuits(for that inexperienced biscuit maker)
directions: Mix well and spoon into muffin tins; bake at 475° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: gary's love mint patties
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together, then add the confectioners sugar.
Mix with a spoon, then knead until mixture is smooth. Divide into 4 parts.
Add coloring, 2 drops at a time.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into shapes or roll into small balls and flatten with fork.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add sherbet last.

title: apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots; cover with water and boil 10 minutes.
Drain, cool and chop fine.
Mix soft butter with sugar and 1 cup sifted flour.
Pack into layer, covering bottom of greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Soften cream cheese in 1-quart mixing bowl on Medium for 1 minute.
Beat in sugar, egg, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line a micro-muffin pan (or 6 custard cups) with paper liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner and fill 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Cook 6 cheesecake cups on Medium for 2 minutes or until nearly set, rotating dish once. Top each with 2 tablespoons of pie filling.
Chill.
May be individually frozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples, chop and set aside.
Pour all Crisco oil into large bowl.
Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Gradually add flour and creamed mixture. Add vanilla, gently fold in apples and pecans.
Pour into a well Pamed 10-inch angel food cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
When cool, remove and drizzle with following glaze.

title: twin meat loaves
directions: Mix meats well.
Stir in onion, celery, salt, poultry seasoning, pepper, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Soak bread in milk.
Add eggs; beat well with rotary beater.
Combine meat and egg mixtures.
Form 2 loaves; roll in bread crumbs. Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Spread 1/2 cup chili sauce over each loaf.
Pour 1/2 cup boiling water around loaves.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sirloin roast
directions: Choose a deep skillet with a lid.
Place it on a stove eye; spray it with cooking oil and pour approximately 1 tablespoon of oil in the bottom.
Brown your roast on both sides.
Put the lid on and bake in your oven for approximately 3 hours at 325°. Remove it from the oven and tear it into serving size pieces or smaller.
Dispose of any fat.
Salt to taste.
Prepare the brown gravy according to the package, usually it is contents of package and 1 cup of water, cooked until thickened.
Add to roast and serve.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine tomato puree, onion and olive oil.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add parsley, oregano, basil and crushed garlic cloves. Also add fennel seed and red pepper.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine
and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Add	flavoring.
Sift
together
flour,
salt and soda. Add flour mixture
and sour cream.	Put in tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, syrup and milk.
Stir until all sugar is dissolved.
As mixture begins to boil, wipe inside of pan with wet cloth to remove any sugar.
Let boil hard until it reaches a soft ball stage.
Add oleo, but do not stir.
Allow to cool.
Add vanilla; beat until stiff.
Pour onto greased platter.
Allow to cool before cutting.
Always let it cool before beating it.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into buttered casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (uncovered).

title: elizabeth's lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in beaten egg yolks and water.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add lemon juice and rind and pour into a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl, stir in remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell. Bake for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 20-30 minutes or until pie tests doen.

title: six week raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Then add flour, soda and salt to wet ingredients. (Add the raisins if you like.) Cover and refrigerate. Bake in muffin tins when needed. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Keeps 6 weeks.

title: date filled brown sugar drop cookies
directions: Make filling first.
Cook over low heat until thickened and add nuts.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar together and drizzle over mixture of lettuce, celery and onion.
Scatter bacon over top of salad.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, sugar, salt, pepper and eggs and mix well.
Add butter and heat until butter is melted, then put in a pan and bake 1 hour in oven at 350° or until done.

title: chili twist
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water with salt, uncovered, until tender.
Drain. Combine with remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sloppy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place chicken in deep casserole dish. Season to taste with lemon pepper.
Mix soup with milk and pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Spread cheese over top of chicken and recover for 10 minutes or until melted. Use soup mixture for sauce and put additional cheese on chicken after serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to boil or until everything is melted and pour over popcorn.
Grease hands and form popcorn balls.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and pie filling.
Add oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Beat at low speed until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes). Add bananas and orange juice.
Beat until well mixed (1 minute). Stir in nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Grease pans.
Makes 3 (5 1/2 x 3-inch) mini loaf pans (35 to 45 minutes) or 1 (9 x 5-inch) pan (60 to 65 minutes).

title: gouchies
directions: Fit crackers on cookie sheet.
Stir sugar into melted margarine.
Cook about 3 minutes over medium heat.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on crackers and pour sugar mixture over each cracker.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Place on wax paper immediately.
Cool completely, then break into pieces.
(Like peanut brittle.)

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Pour over cabbage and mix.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Dip rolls in mixture.
Place in broiler pan, seam side up. Top with small amount of melted butter.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour pineapple over bottom and cover with blueberries. Sprinkle with sugar.
Next, sprinkle dry cake mix over top of sugar.
Pour melted oleo over all. Sprinkle with pecans and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until done. Serve plain or with ice cream or whipped cream on top.

title: hershey's lite chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa and soda.
Melt butter.
Stir in sugar, then add milk, vinegar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Put in flat glass dish or pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cloud 9 pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust (or bake pie crust).
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs, if desired.
Chill several hours and serve.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook chicken in hot oil.
Add peppers, carrots and garlic; cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce; add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar and ginger.
Bring to a full boil.
Serve over brown rice.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning.
Layer in a 11 x 8 x 2-inch pan in following order:
cream cheese, hamburger with seasoning and hot Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with Doritos chips.

title: daffodil dream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Put next 3 ingredients in a bowl. Stir. Blend into saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thick. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in butter and lemon juice. Blend. Refrigerate approximately 45 minutes.
Fold in yogurt.
Add coloring.

title: simply delicious cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling and crushed pineapple with juice in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with nuts. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: overnight cinnamon coffeecake
directions: In a greased Bundt pan, place half of the frozen dough balls, powdered pudding mix, brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and pecans. Repeat with remaining dough balls and pudding mix, brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and pecans.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Cook cornbread and crumble into crock-pot.
Put chopped onion, celery, eggs and cans of soup into crock-pot.
Pour chicken broth and chicken pieces over cornbread mixture.
Put sage, salt and pepper to your taste.
Cook on low for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon-lime mold
directions: Prepare lemon jello according to directions on package and pour into mold.
Prepare lime jello using 7-Up to replace water.
Pour lime jello mixture into bowl and chill for 2 hours.
Remove lime jello from refrigerator and add Cool Whip.
Mix until well blended. Smooth lime mixture over lemon jello and allow to set 2 to 4 hours. Remove from mold; garnish with lemon and lime slices and pieces of fresh mint.
A cool, easy dessert great for summer!

title: chocolate crunch
directions: Place melted butter, flour and 1 cup pecans in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix well with fork, then mash down with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until slightly brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and small Cool Whip until creamy.
Spread over pudding.
Spread over cooled crust.
Fix pudding according to directions and pour over cheese mixture.
Allow pudding to set up and cover with large Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.

title: special chicken(eileen says, "this is good")
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place a layer of dried beef in bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken breast halves on top of dried beef.
Place 1 slice of bacon on each chicken half.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over the ingredients in the casserole dish.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Coat a 2-quart casserole dish with Pam cooking spray.
Combine broccoli and onions. Cook according to package directions.
Drain well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs gradually. Beat in sugar, then oil.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients.

Add to first mixture alternately with zucchini. Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla. Turn into two greased and lightly floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 2-inch). Bake on lowest rack at 350° for about 55 minutes or until loaves test done.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool.
Dust top with confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 loaves. Freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour into a square 2-quart round buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs and dot with butter.
(Frozen broccoli can be cooked according to package directions and drained well before mixing with other ingredients.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chuckwagon beef bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large skillet until hot and bubbly. Reduce heat.
Separate 1 can biscuits and place 1-inch cube of Cheddar cheese in each.
Fold in half; press firmly.
Drop biscuits in one tablespoon of milk, then roll in crushed corn chips.
Pour hot mixture ina 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 18 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together in large bowl the Crisco, sugars, egg, water and vanilla. Beat thoroughly.

title: stolen squash
directions: Go gather some squash out of Rick's garden when he's not home. Clean and cut into medium pieces to boil.
Boil until real tender and drain.
Fry in skillet with butter until it turns a light brown.
Salt and pepper to taste and serve.
This dish is very good and cheap!
Then you can have your pastor over for supper.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls to make 4 rectangles per package. Spread 2
heaping tablespoonfuls of sausage on each rectangle and roll up.
Place
on a baking sheet and freeze until firm. Remove
from freezer; slice into 1/2-inch pinwheels and store in freezer bags in freezer until ready to serve.

title: brownies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Sift the flour, cocoa and pinch of salt together. Add the dry mixture with the egg mixture. Add the nuts.
Grease pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer chopped vegetables in bowl. Combine salad dressing, sugar and a little vinegar. Spread over top and sprinkle with cheese. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight. Toss just before serving.

title: slush
directions: Soak tea bags in boiling water for 30 minutes.
Add apricot brandy, lemonade, orange juice, sugar and water.
Freeze this mixture.
With an ice cream scoop, put mix in glass and fill glass up with 7-Up or ginger ale.
Great to keep on hand for unexpected guests.
(Will keep for up to a year.)

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Mix cheeses, mayo and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add drained spinach.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon on top!
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with thin slices of French bread.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy; add Cool Whip.
Put into crust and place pie filling on top.
Chill and serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Use as a dip for cauliflower, celery, carrots and bell pepper or with shrimp.

title: french zucchini soup
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add zucchini and shallots. Cook until soft, about 10 minutes.
Add 2 cups of chicken broth, curry and cayenne pepper.
Pour into blender and puree.
For more thickness, add 2 to 3 tablespoons potato flakes.
Return to pot and add 2 more cups of chicken broth.
Cook for 5 more minutes. Serve and garnish with croutons.
Serves 4.

title: no peek chicken and rice
directions: Grease large baking pan; sprinkle rice into pan.
Season raw chicken and place on top of rice.
Mix soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Lipton soup over top.
Cover tightly and bake 2 hours.

title: no-bake fudge nuggets
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and boil 1 minute (full, rolling boil).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours at room temperature.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix canned ingredients and onion in pan.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In a buttered casserole dish, crumble Doritos and layer with creamed ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly in center.

title: orange pound cake with icing
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream
butter
and
Crisco; then add sugar and eggs one at a
time.
Add
dry	ingredients
and
milk alternately (starting and
ending with flour).
Put in cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 50 minutes or until done.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and onion rings (1/2 can).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: russian potato salad
directions: Mix beets and potatoes.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Let stand a few hours.
Just before serving, add the ham and cheese.
Toss well and serve at once.

title: marinated baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a flat baking dish in a single layer.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken; marinate for at least one hour in refrigerator.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until meat is tender, turning once during cooking.

title: butler's crab casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add milk and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; add egg yolks, then crabmeat.
Pour into a casserole.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add corn, milk and muffin mix. Melt margarine in 9 x 12 casserole dish in oven.
Remove and add all other ingredients.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla.
Roll dough into tube shape (to be sliced) and roll into damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator overnight.	Slice thin and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix shortening in milk.
Add cold water, sugar and salt. Dissolve yeast in tablespoon of warm water.
Add to mixture and then add flour.
Store in refrigerator.
Roll and cut about 2 hours before cooking.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk, baking soda, salt, cooking oil and creamed corn together; set aside.
Brown the following: hamburger, onion and dried red pepper flakes or jalapeno peppers. Take off heat and add Cheddar cheese.

title: german grebble
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat again.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Add enough of the flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out on a floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 3 x 4-inch squares.
Make 2 slits in each square.
Pull one corner through opposite slit.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides, like doughnuts.
Roll in sugar.

title: kraft warm honey dijon chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, honey, mustard and tarragon; reserve 1/2 cup. Pour remaining mayonnaise mixture over chicken in shallow baking dish; cover.
Refrigerate 20 minutes or overnight to marinade. Drain.
Discard marinade.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Heat oven
to
In
a medium bowl, combine 1/4 of the soup with remaining ingredients, except water.
Mix well. Shape into
patties.
Arrange	in
single
layer
in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Skim off fat.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Pour into three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and save juice.
Add egg and flour; pepper to taste (no salt).
Add baking powder to 1/4 cup juice.
Should fill cup to 3/4 full with foam.
Mix.
Form into patties and fry.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, egg and sugar together.
Sift flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon and mix with first 3 ingredients.
Add applesauce and baking soda.
Drop tablespoons onto greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Adjust time for larger size cookie.

title: stuffed hamburger buns
directions: Grind up all ingredients and mix with tomato sauce.
Remove a small amount of dough from the center of the hamburger buns.
Fill the bun with filling.
Wrap with aluminum foil.
When ready to serve, heat in a moderate oven, bun and foil, until hot all the way through.
The cheese melts into the ingredients.
Delicious.

title: tracey's mexican casserole
directions: Tear tortillas and line 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown hamburger meat.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Pour over tortillas.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls on the bottom of a small cookie sheet. (Fold ends if necessary.)
Bake according to directions.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, Ranch dressing and garlic powder.
Spread this mixture on the baked crescent rolls.
Top with some of the following:
green olives, shredded carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, green peppers, celery, etc.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: peanut butter round-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop or roll in balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies and bake 12 minutes.

title: no fail pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour into deep pie crust. Bake 30 min. at 350°.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 loaf metal loaf pan.

In a medium bowl combine first 5 ingredients. Grate 1 tbsp of peel and squeeze 3 tbsp of juice from the lemons. In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat margarine or butter with 1 1/2 cups sugar until blended, at high speed beat until light, about 5 minutes, add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in the lemon peel and vanilla.
At low speed, alternately add flour mixture and sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Spoon batter into pan and bake 1 hour 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Mix lemon juice and 1/3 cup sugar, brush over top and sides of warm cake.
Cool completely.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pretzel strawberry dessert
directions: Break up pretzels into bite-sizes and place on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour melted margarine over pretzels and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate to cool.

title: dirt cake(good gift idea)
directions: You will need 1 gallon size Baggie, 1 large new clay flower pot, 1 bunch artificial flowers and 1 piece aluminum foil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain.
Add all ingredients, except half of butter and cracker crumbs.
Stir and pour into baking dish.
Add crumbled crackers; dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until brown on top.

title: aunt sherry's special spinach pie
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add squash and cook until tender. Add all other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs, that are mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg, vanilla and lemon flavoring. Add the flour alternately with the milk.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Do not open the oven while cake is cooking.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 9 x 13 pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top evenly with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a very large mixing bowl. This is important because the recipe is large. Add beaten eggs, shortening and buttermilk. Mix well and store in a covered glass or plastic container in the refrigerator. Use as desired.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash yams.
Add butter, sugar, milk, salt and rind.
With a tablespoon, scoop up about 1/4 cup of mixture and shape around marshmallow, using more potatoes as needed to make balls.
Roll each ball in cornflakes.
Place on a buttered baking dish; cover with foil and freeze.
When ready to serve, bake until marshmallows begin to ooze, about 20 minutes.

title: northwest dip
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese and heavy cream together until smooth and creamy. Stir in the onion, lemon juice and red pepper sauce. Gently fold in the smoked salmon and mashed avocado, being careful not to overmix. Serve with cucumber, celery, your choice of low-carb crackers or pork rinds. Yield: 6 servings.

title: hurry-up caramel buns
directions: Allow the frozen bread dough to thaw following the package directions.

title: coal miners cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot and spicy chicken
directions: Note:
Amount depends on number to feed.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, water, pudding mix, and bananas; blend well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in spices; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Grease and flour 10 inch tube pan; fill with batter and bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes and turn on rack to cool completely. Dust with powdered sugar and serve.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put in glass container or old timey churn to soak.
Add 1 cup salt to 1 gallon water and place over cucumbers.
Soak 1 week.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix ingredients together in large pan or bowl and cut butter in.
Mix well 4 1/2 cups sugar and 1 tall can Pet milk.
Boil exactly 6 minutes.
This all that is cooked.
Pour over mixture and stir until marshmallows are dissolved.
Pour in greased pan and cool.
No beating required.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: cheese dip
directions: Add ground beef and mix well.

title: flan
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a blender.
Make caramel crust by dissolving white sugar in a small pan until light brown.
Pour into deep baking dish.
Pour other mixture over crust.
Bake in pan of water for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine or butter with graham cracker crumbs and place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks of margarine and powdered sugar for exactly 15 minutes.
Spread on top of crumbs.
Slice bananas and place over mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas and top with Dream Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts on top.

title: foolproof pie crust(makes 5 shells)
directions: With fork, stir together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In small bowl beat together water, vinegar and eggs.
Add to flour mixture until moist.
Divide into 5 pieces.
Chill at least 1/2 hour.
Roll out into pie plates.
Crust may be frozen until ready to use.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Put into a large bowl.
Bring oleo, cocoa, Mazola and water to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs and mix well. Add milk.
Cook in double boiler or on direct heat, stirring constantly. When the filling thickens, remove from heat and cool.
Add flavoring. Alternate wafers, sliced bananas and filling in dish until full.

title: lasagna #2
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer, uncovered until thick, 45 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato casserole souffl
directions: Combine potatoes and all ingredients.
Mix well and spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: oklahoma cowboy stew
directions: Dredge meat in plastic sack with generous amount of flour (to thicken stew).
Brown in Dutch oven in Wesson oil (not enough to make greasy).
Turn to brown.
Add 1 tablespoon chili sauce and 1 teaspoon chili powder.
Add water to cover all vegetables.
Stir to keep from sticking in pan.
Turn stove to low heat until done. Just before serving, add 1 can green peas, drained.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve with cornbread or garlic bread.
Add more veggies, if need larger.

title: chicken corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour, pepper and celery salt.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil 1 minute.
Combine sauce with chicken and corn.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix above and form into balls.
Brown in a little oil.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add egg.
Add flour and baking soda.
Add potato chips and chocolate chips. Bake for 10 to 11 minutes at 350° two inches apart on greased sheet.
Cool for 30 seconds on sheet, then 5 minutes on rack. Store in airtight container.

title: green bean treat
directions: Drain green beans.
Place in 1 1/2-quart covered casserole. Sprinkle with salt and spread soup over beans.
Place in Radarange oven for 5 minutes.
Place onion rings on top and continue to cook for 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: no sugar corn flake crust
directions: Mix butter and sweetener.
Add crumbs.
Stir well.
Press about 2/3 of crumbs in bottom and sides of 9-inch pie shell, using another pie pan to press in well.
Chill well before filling. Reserve rest of crumbs to sprinkle on top of pie.

title: nanny's date cake
directions: Sift 1/2 of the flour with soda, salt and spices.
Use other half to dredge dates and nuts.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and buttermilk slowly.
Mix well, then add nuts and dates.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 1 hour.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes. Add egg and shortening.
Mix in remaining flour.
Mix with hands until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and grease top.
Cover with damp cloth.
Punch down occasionally. Refrigerate.
Use as needed.
Makes 2 batches.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in roasting pan and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Then cook, covered, in 275° oven for 12 hours.
Remove from oven and shred with fork.

title: jalapeno buffalo burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties about 1/2 inch thick.
Set oven control to broil.
Place patties on rack in broiler pan.
Broil with tops about 3 inches from heat for 4 to 6 minutes, turning once.
Serve with salsa, taco sauce or chili sauce.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil until vegetables are tender. Add water, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce to desired taste and thickness.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add green peppers, onions and celery and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly. Add canned tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, bay leaf and parsley.
Bring to boil, simmer for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf and add Worcestershire sauce and shrimp.
Heat until shrimp are hot.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and egg, blend until creamy.
Blend in pumpkin.
Combine flour, soda, nutmeg, ginger and cinnamon together and sift into egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add chocolate chips, or nuts can be used instead.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes if using 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
If using 4 mini loaf pans, bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese evenly over bottom of pan (greased 9 to 10-inch pie dish).
Blend the milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper in blender at high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fish pudding(fiske pudding)
directions: Put fish through food grinder and grind several times until very fine.
Stir in seasonings and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating in thoroughly.
Add softened butter, then the cream, beating until light and fluffy.
Turn into buttered mold; set in pan of hot water and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about one hour.
Slice and serve with a cream sauce or a cream shrimp sauce.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Steam shrimp half the normal time since they will cook more in the quiche.
Peel shrimp and marinate half the shrimp in the dressing.
Prick pie shell and bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes. Melt the butter in a skillet and saute green onion, celery and mushrooms.	In a separate bowl, beat egg with whisk.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce, Parmesan cheese and crabmeat.
Then add 1 cup of the cheddar cheese, the plain shrimp, and the sauteed mixture.
Drain marinating shrimp with a slotted spoon and add them to the mixture.	Pour into the baked pie shell and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add remaining cheddar cheese on top and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a 9 X 13 Pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer ten minutes before serving.

title: fruit and cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, pudding and juice in food processor.
Add by hand the fruit cocktail.
Form into ball.
Cover with almonds.
Chill. Serve surrounded by gingersnaps.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are done and golden brown.
Mix dressing, bacon, eggs, onions, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Add potatoes; mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Cover bottom of buttered baking dish with crushed crackers, then a layer of oysters.
Dot with butter and seasoning.
Make another layer of crumbs and another of oysters.
Dot with butter. Pour the liquids over top; sprinkle with butter and bread crumbs. Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add bananas and eggs.
Stir in flour and nutmeg.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water; stir in vanilla. Combine all ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter.
Gradually add whipped cream and powdered sugar.
Put in 2 (9-inch) graham cracker pie shells.
Put chocolate shaving on top if desired.
Put in refrigerator for at least 8 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine beef, soup mix, bread crumbs and milk.
Place beef mixture in baking dish (bread loaf dish).
Spread ketchup across top, thin layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix dressing with macaroni, then cool.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and mustard and add to macaroni.
Put in refrigerator one hour to chill.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Beat 4 to 5 minutes.
Add vanilla as you beat.
Pour into tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook the shrimp in boiling water with the bay leaf, pickling spice and vinegar.
Cook until shells turn pink, about 15 minutes. Drain and cover with cold water.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Prepare fresh bread crumbs by processing French bread in food processor, using steel blade.
(Dry packaged bread crumbs will not work.)
Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Slather chicken liberally with Dijon mustard.
Dip chicken into fresh bread crumbs.
Place chicken into a baking dish oiled with olive oil.
Melt butter and drizzle over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, rolled oats and cinnamon.
Add melted butter; set aside. Peel apples and slice up in pieces.
Grease a 9 x 13 1/2-inch pan; put apples on bottom.
Put mixture over apples. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Salad: Combine spinach, mushrooms, onions and eggs.

title: creole smothered chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper and roll in flour. Brown well in a little shortening in large pot or skillet.
Remove and add chopped vegetables in remaining shortening (add more if needed) and cook until wilty tender.
Place chicken back in pot/skillet and add 1/2 cup of water and cover.
Cook on low until chicken is tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour, adding more water if needed.
Add pepper seasoning and chopped, fresh parsley during last 30 minutes of cooking.
The gravy from this dish is excellent with rice.

title: most requested cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While warm, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Spread entire can of caramel icing over warm cake.
Refrigerate until cool.
Mix Heath bits and crushed Nestle Crunch bar with Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put all ingredients into a 2 1/2-quart pan. Cook over very low flame. Stir often. Cook until almost all milk is gone.
When almost cool, beat 1 egg and mix in well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add egg, sugar, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into segments.
Dip strips into melted oleo before placing into pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot turkey
directions: Place turkey breast in crock-pot.
Add 1 cup water.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Cook 12 hours on low setting. Meat will fall easily from bone.
Place meat on platter.
Strain broth and serve over rice.

title: stir fry
directions: Layer wok or large skillet with olive oil and brown the chopped onions or garlic. (Each adds a different overall flavor to recipe and burning either is not good.)

Add diced chicken and cook until done. Turn burner to a medium heat and mix in your vegetables adding those which take the longest to soften first carrots. Pour in a little water to steam the vegetables and keep everything from burning. Cover (but stir periodically) and allow to simmer until vegetables are softened to your taste. Serve over rice with desired stir-fry sauce.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Soak pared and sliced cucumbers in water for 3 hours.
Mix sour cream with next ingredients.
Drain cucumbers and add to sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle on some parsley and chill.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apple filling in buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add sweetened condensed milk, melted butter or margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well.
Pour over apple filling.

title: chicken-vegetable casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 3 cups of Stove Top stuffing dry mix that has been mixed with 1 1/2 cups water or broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best yet cake
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: whipped topping (dieters)
directions: *Place a few ice cubes in water until ice cold.
This is essential for proper whipping.

title: country coconut pie
directions: Mix
well.
Pour
into unbaked pie shell and bake until firm. Remove
from oven.
Beat egg whites with a little sugar and spread
over
pie;
sprinkle
a
little coconut over pie. Return to oven and bake until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: *If making a coconut pie use 3/4 cup or can of coconut.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add 1 cup of pecans and mix well. Refrigerate until firm, then shape into ball.
Roll in remaining pecans before serving and garnish as desired.
Serve with a variety of crackers.
Delicious!

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, shortening, milk and molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, add vanilla and oats.
Roll out and cut with a cookie cutter.
Don't roll too thin.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple pie for one
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Brown apple in melted margarine with brown sugar and apple pie spice.
Stuff into the 1 ounce pita bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Put chestnuts, bamboo shoots, onion, mushrooms, celery, bean sprouts and shrimp in boiling water and cook until tender.
Allow to cool (if you use canned water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, mushrooms, bean sprouts and cooked shrimp; they do not need to cook with celery and onion).
Drain.
Add salt, sugar, Accent and chicken.
Mix well.
Place a rounded tablespoonful in center of egg roll wrapper and fold up.
Dip the egg roll in unbeaten egg white and deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce, soy sauce or hot mustard.
Makes about 14 large egg rolls.
Use as appetizer.
Cut into pieces.
Should be served hot.
Best if made and fried fresh.
But can be made early in day and fried later. Freeze before cooking.

title: spinach, mushroom and cheddar frittata
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle mushrooms, spinach and cheese in pie plate.
Put milk, Bisquick and eggs into blender on high speed until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie plate and bake for 30 to 35 minutes (no longer).
It is important to let Frittata cool for 10 to 15 minutes in order to set.
Slice and serve with your favorite salad.

title: yellow-crooked neck squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: egg noodles with tuna fish
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Separate tuna into flakes.
Mix with cream of mushroom soup, milk and seasonings.
Bake in moderate 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: corn pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie shell with corn filling and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: baked potato topping
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with hot or cold roast beef or as a topping for baked potatoes.

title: one-dish spaghetti
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1-quart microwave-safe casserole; add onion.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir to break meat into small pieces.
Add tomato sauce, water and spaghetti.
Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High 10 to 11 minutes or until spaghetti is tender, stirring twice.
Serve with Parmesan cheese. Makes about 2 servings, 275 calories each.

title: dip for chips
directions: You may want more horseradish to suit your taste.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Fold in drained pineapple.
Line 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with half of the crushed wafers.
Place pineapple mixture on wafers, then remaining wafers on top.
Add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Let set in icebox for two or three hours before serving.

title: homemade glitter
directions: Stir the ingredients well.
Cook the ingredients in the microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread the glitter mixture on waxed paper and let it dry.
Store in airtight containers until the kids are ready to use it.
Substitute sugar for salt, and use the sugar for decorating cookies or cakes.

title: banana bread
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Melt butter, combine with cake mix, eggs, water, vanilla and bananas.
Beat about 4 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Pour mixture on top of melted margarine in pan.
Sprinkle 2 cups grated cheese on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: orange poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese product, margarine and 1 cup sugar in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Mix together flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to cream cheese mixture alternately with sour half and half.
