Stir in poppy seed and orange peel.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all; press into ungreased Pyrex loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for about 1 hour.
Can sprinkle Parmesan cheese before you bake.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine and chips; add peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Stir until coated.
Place in garbage bag with 4 cups confectioners' sugar.
Shake until coated.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind or grate squash, pepper and onions.
Mix with salt and ice water to cover vegetables.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Rinse well and drain thoroughly.
In saucepan, put sugar, vinegar, water, turmeric and celery seed.
Add vegetables and simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon piping hot into jars and seal. Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
This relish is sweet and good eating with meat.
Makes 10 pints.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix Sugar, Butter and Eggs.
Add smashed Bananas and Water.
Sift the Flour, Baking Soda, Baking Powder and Salt.
Add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake 1 hour or until tooth pick comes out clean.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add milk, making thin batter. Place butter in an 8-inch baking dish and melt.
Pour the thin batter over melted butter.
Do not stir! Place 2 cups fruit of your choice (fresh or canned, drained) over the batter and sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar or less.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine cumin, oregano, paprika, chili and sugar in a small bowl.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet.
Add onion, pepper, chiles, lime juice and salt.
Saute slowly for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add garlic and cilantro.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Increase heat to high.
Add chicken and spice to pan and saute until chicken is lightly brown.
Season to taste with salt. Steam tortillas.
Roll chicken mixture into tortillas and top with condiments of your choice.

title: green chili hors d'oeuvres
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Chop and mix green chiles into cream cheese.
Spread chile and cheese mixture on flour tortillas.
Roll tortillas.
Refrigerate for at least an hour to set.
Cut each roll into 6 pieces with a very sharp knife.

title: hot and spicy marinated vegetables
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside. Combine vinegar, garlic powder and oils; stir well. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables; toss gently to coat. Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 8 hours, tossing occasionally. Serve with a slotted spoon. Yields 4 servings (30 calories and 45% fat per 1/2 cup serving).

title: nut cups
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together, then mix in flour. Chill 15 minutes.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with small glass.
Line muffin pans.
Pour in filling and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon four-layer delight
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix together the first 3 ingredients; press on the bottom of the greased dish.
Cook at 375° for 15 minutes, or until brown.
Cool completely.

title: peach slush
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze for 24 hours.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again.
With wire whisk, stir in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in pecans. Pour into crust and bake for 50 minutes.

title: whipped dip(for fruit)
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a blender.
Garnish with an orange twist.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Place rice in bottom of dish and place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top of chicken.
Lastly, pour water over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with 2 cups of Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: seafood baked potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients with scooped out potatoes and put back in the shells. (If too dry, add a little milk.) Bake stuffed shells in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach helen
directions: Cook spinach in as little water as possible.
Drain off liquid.
Mix dry onion soup mix and lemon juice into sour cream and blend into hot spinach.
Turn into heated casserole and place in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly and leave crisp.
Then mix the rest of the ingredients and fold in small broccoli flowerets.
Put in casserole or a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex.
Breadcrumbs can be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer if desired.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate bits over low heat.
Add peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: chicken broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stuffing, together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle herb seasoned stuffing over mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine and drizzle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large pot, cook bacon until golden brown; add onion and celery and saute until soft and transparent.
Add clam juice, clams, potatoes and seasonings; cook until potatoes are tender. Slowly stir in cream; heat through but do not boil.
Serve hot with oyster crackers.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Flour meat; brown in oil.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: volcano cake(bubbles when baking)
directions: Place coconut and pecans in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to box directions and pour into pan.
Mix melted butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over batter and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss steak ala pat
directions: Put shortening in pan.
Cube steak in about 1-inch squares. Flour steak cubes and brown them in the shortening.
Add tomato sauce and one can of water.
Slice onion and add to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat. Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: bean salad
directions: In a large bowl mix beans, onion and pepper.
In a jar, mix vinegar, oil, sugar and celery seed.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables and stir lightly.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine Pudding, milk, chocolate chips and butter in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil. Remove from heat. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into shell and chill 3 hours. Garnish with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate curls or grated chocolate.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Put grated cabbage into a large container.
Do not pack. Arrange onion rings on top.

title: roll-out cookie recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, cream butter or oleo and sugar with electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour (one cup at a time).
Mix after each addition. The dough will be very stiff.
Blend last flour by hand.
Do not chill.
Divide into 2 balls.
On floured surface, roll each ball in circle approximately 12 inches in diameter and 1/8-inch thick. Use cutters as a guide.
Dough should only be slightly thinner than cutter.
Dip cutters in flour before each use.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet on middle rack of oven for 6 to 10 minutes or slightly browned.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together.
Pour over sugar.
Add flour, alternating with the eggs.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Add jello. Cool.
Mix with strawberries and pour into baked pie shell. Chill.

title: cheesy mcbrandon
directions: Fry burgers in Worcestershire sauce.
Drain.
Place burgers in buns with cheese on each side.
Add bacon strips and barbecue sauce.
Enjoy!!!!

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Arrange apples in greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Mix flour, oats, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Add butter and mix. Sprinkle over apples and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in large pan.
Add chopped bell pepper, chopped onion and chopped celery.
Add other ingredients and season with chili powder to taste.
Cook 1 hour on low heat after it comes to a boil.

title: sliced apples
directions: Combine first four ingredients; bring to boil and add food coloring and sliced apples.
Cook until tender.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with more cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Mix caramel candy in double boiler and add milk.
Melt fully and add pecans.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Let cool in refrigerator for 1 hour or overnight.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Put each piece of candy in chocolate and place back on wax paper to cool.

title: jello punch
directions: Bring water to a boil; add jello and sugar.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Pour into gallon jar and finish filling jar with cold water.
Freeze.
Add ginger ale when served.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Grate onion, sweet pepper and carrot.
Put into a bowl.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and spices over all; mix well. Pour vinegar over and mix again.
Place in covered container and let stand 24 hours.
Will keep 3 weeks in a covered container.

title: lunch room rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar and oil.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut
and place in buttered
pan.
Let rise for at least
minutes
before putting into oven at 400°.
Bake until
golden
brown;
butter tops.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanuts until smooth, then stir in peanuts.
Chill.
Peel apples just before serving.
Arrange around dip.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, soda and applesauce.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Use 1/2 cup of the dressing mix.
Let cheeses set at room temperature for 1 hour.
Mix dressing and Cheddar cheese with electric mixer.
Blend in cream cheese.
Cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Shape and roll in nuts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat; drain and add Ro-Tel.
Mix sugar, cornmeal, eggs, milk, baking soda, salt, corn and bacon grease in large bowl.
In iron skillet, brown 2 tablespoons cornmeal.
Pour 1/2 of mix into skillet.
Then layer meat, onion and cheese.
Pour remaining mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix as for any pound cake.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes after taking out of the oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add some onion.
Simmer hamburger, spaghetti sauce and tomato paste. Pour hamburger mixture on bottom of pan. Put layer of noodles, layer of cheese, layer of hamburger, noodles and cheese.
Be sure to put layer of hamburger on bottom and layer of cheese on top or noodles will burn.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: forever wedding cake(makes one happy marriage)
directions: Combine true love, rounded cup perfect trust, pinch of unselfishness, a portion of interest in all he does and pint of sympathy and understanding.
Flavor with cheerful home and many loving kisses. Mix well.
Bake all your life.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add water, Miracle Whip and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: lime pineapple jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O as directed on package except use ice cubes instead of cold water for quick set.
After Jell-O is set, pour into bowl and mix with Cool Whip.
After mixed well, add drained, crushed pineapple.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate until set.

title: old-fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs, beating after each.
Add butter and buttermilk.
Brush pastry with butter before pouring in custard.
Bake at 375° until firm.

title: brown rice
directions: Bake in covered ovenproof dish at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh carrot cake
directions: Beat together corn oil, sugar and eggs until well combined. In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat together with the sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in the vanilla and mix well.
Add the carrots, walnuts, coconut and pineapple. Mix until well blended.
Pour batter into a greased and floured
9 or 10-inch Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until a tester inserted near the center comes out clean. Don't overbake or it will be dry.
Cook on cake rack.
Remove from pan.
Cover with Cream Cheese Icing.
Garnish with grated carrots and/or chopped nuts and currants.

title: montana spice cookies
directions: Combine water and raisins; cook until water is absorbed.
Add the soda.
Cream together sugar and shortening; add the eggs.
Mix together salt, flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add creamed mixture; add raisins last.
Form into balls and flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 375° oven about 10 minutes.

title: easy beef and salsa burritos
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix in seasonings.
Stir in spinach and salsa.
Heat through.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on the package.
Bake in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in the pan 15 minutes.
Then poke holes with a fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
(Use a meat fork, if possible.)
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add the cold water and pour over the cake.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Then frost with Cool Whip.

title: cabbage crunch salad
directions: Crush the noodles up in small pieces while still in the package.

title: cabbage and smoked sausage
directions: Quarter cabbage and potatoes.
Cut carrots in 1-inch pieces. Cook in water with Hillshire smoked sausage, cut in 1-inch pieces, until tender.
Drain off vegetables, saving 3/4 cup broth.
Mix flour, sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper and cook until thick with 3/4 cup broth.
Pour over vegetables and sausage.

title: garlic bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening and sugar.
Add yeast when mixture is lukewarm. Add 3 cups flour; beat thoroughly. Set in warm place for 30 minutes or until dough raises.
Beat eggs, salt, onion and garlic.
Add to mixture along with remaining flour.
Knead until dough is no longer sticky.
Let raise until double in size.
Break into 2 pieces and place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Keep pieces separate.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine.
Take knife, dip in margarine and cut slices in dough.
Pour remaining margarine on dough. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey chex no-bake drop cookies
directions: Bring honey and sugar to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Stir in Corn Chex.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: 4 minute microwave fudge
directions: Place sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa in a glass mixing bowl.
Do not mix.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Mix well and stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly buttered 8 x 8-inch dish and refrigerate 5 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, salt and water.
Bring mixture to a boil. Prepare cucumbers and fill jars.
Place 1 dill head, grape leaf and separated garlic clove into each jar.
Pour boiling mixture on top and seal each jar tightly.
Turn upside-down so liquid gets to garlic and dill.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Heat first four ingredients together to melt candy in 2-quart saucepan.
Add orange juice and lemonade.
Remove from heat.
Mix with 1 part water and 1 part tea.

title: low-fat broccoli soup
directions: Peel thick stalks of broccoli; chop stalks and heads (about 4 cups).
In 3-quart saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cook, uncovered, just until tender.
Drain, reserving 2 cups liquid.
In blender, place broccoli mixture and milk. Cover and blend until smooth; set aside.

title: cheese balls
directions: Stir together in bowl flour, red pepper and salt.
Cream in butter.
Add cheese and Rice Krispies and blend well.
Roll into small balls (about 1/2-inch diameter).
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Yield: about 100.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add pepper, seasonings, tomato sauce, tomato paste, chopped tomato and cottage cheese.
Simmer on low heat while noodles cook.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix sugar, water and tea bags in large pan.
Heat until hot but not boiling
and
add
orange
juice
(adding required water as noted on
cans), pineapple juice, lemon juice, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Now bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for about an hour.	Spices	will
settle to the bottom, so you will need to strain
tea
to
remove all at once.
This makes about 1 1/2 to 2 gallons and will keep in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all but pineapple, beat well (will be thick).
Add pineapple.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together sugar, peanut butter and melted butter.
Shape into small balls.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs together. Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ballard's fruitcake
directions: Use a large mixing bowl to mix the fruit, pecans and coconut in.
Add the condensed milk and mix well.
Bake in a paper lined tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz and melt. Then add steamed broccoli and cooked rice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Drain.
Add 1/2 pound cheese in chunks; melt.
Put cheese-meat mixture in flour tortillas.
Arrange tortillas in single layer in baking dish and cover with white cheese sauce.
Bake 20 minutes at 320°.

title: dill dip
directions: Dip can be made the day before.
When ready to serve, slice top from bread, scoop out soft bread, leaving shell.

title: party cheese straws
directions: Allow shredded cheese and margarine to reach room temperature. Toast sesame seed in heavy skillet on low heat, about 20 minutes, until brown.
Cool.

title: layered tostada bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease large rectangular glass baking dish (12 x 7 1/2-inch).
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, beans, chilies and olives.
Mix baking mix, cornmeal, milk, 1 egg and oil until moistened; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Spread in dish. Spoon beef mixture over dough.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over beef mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: old-fashioned chicken stew
directions: Heat the oil in a large kettle or Dutch oven over medium high heat.
Saute onions; stir until soft, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cubed chicken and garlic; continue to cook and stir for about 5 minutes longer.
Pour in chicken broth and water; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a simmer and cook for 30 to 40 minutes. Stew should simmer without boiling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: betty browns
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except apples and nuts.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: kielbasi and sauce
directions: Blend jelly, mustard and cornstarch.
Bake kielbasi with water for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into little pieces.
Pour sauce on top or keep warm in small crock-pot.
Retrieve with toothpicks.

title: new year's black-eyed peas
directions: Slice sausage thin.
Stir into tomato sauce.
Add onion and spices.
Cook 30 minutes on medium heat.
Add rice and black-eyed peas.
Continue to cook until rice and meat are tender.

title: chicken with stuffing
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place slice of cheese on top of each piece.
Stir soup and wine together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken.
Melt margarine and drizzle over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade strawberry jam
directions: Place all ingredients
in a nonaluminum pot or frying pan (melt butter first).
Bring to rolling boil; cook 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken and pour into stainless bowl and allow to cool overnight.
When cool, stir again.
If thick as you like, reheat mixture and pour hot jam into sterile jelly jars. Seal with paraffin.
Yields 4 pints.
Try this with fresh peaches, also!

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil, then remove from heat. Add 1 cup (6 ounces) chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chocolate morsels and nuts.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until brown.
Add all ingredients, except cheese and noodles.
Cook noodles according to directions. Put a layer of meat mixture in baking dish, then shredded cheese, then noodles.
Repeat again, ending with meat mixture, topped with cheese.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: easy beef stir fry
directions: Cut steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices. Sprinkle with salt & pepper. Saute garlic for 30 seconds. Add beef, cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in soy sauce. Stir together beef broth and cornstarch until smooth. Add to beef, and cook 1 minute or until thickened, stirring constantly. Add green onion. Serve immediately over hot cooked rice.

title: soul wings
directions: Arrange chicken wings
in
shallow
baking
dish.
Heat butter, soy sauce, sugar,
water
and mustard until butter and sugar are melted.
Season chicken with red pepper.
Cool sugar mixture;
pour over wings and marinate at least 2 hours.
Turn once or twice.
Bake at 375°
for 1 1/2 hours.
Place on paper towel to drain.
Use Blue
cheese
dressing for dip.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook beef until brown; drain fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: red kidney beans and rice
directions: Soak the beans overnight or bring to a boil and soak for 1 hour.
Drain; place in large pot with water to cover and simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Add seasonings and cook until beans are soft, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with hot rice.
Serves 5 or 6 people.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, margarine and pecans; press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on crust. Mix vanilla pudding with milk. Spread on top of cream cheese layer Cool Whip on top of pudding. Chill for several hours.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding eggs in 1 at a time.
Mix with mixer on high.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in tube cake pan which has been greased and floured.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water until dissolved.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour onto well floured surface.
Press well.
Cut into circles and place in well greased pan.
Spread butter on rolls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Slice angel food cake in half.
Drain fruit cocktail, mix with Cool Whip and spread between layers and on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Cook rice; add soups to onion and celery and heat, then combine rice and broccoli.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cocoa in the pan.
Stir until fully blended.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Add peanut butter, butter and oatmeal.
Stir until all of the oatmeal has been coated.
Spoon drop onto wax paper.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Then add eggs and melted chocolate.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with ice water to first part.
Bake in 14 1/2 x 10 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet.
When meat is done, dip meat out of the grease with a slotted spoon.
Meat may be patted on paper towels to remove even more grease.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole pan.
Place a layer of hamburger, then a layer of potatoes and onions.
Keep layering until all the hamburger and potatoes and onions are used.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix milk and soup together; pour over top of casserole. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about an hour or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: veggie medley
directions: *Squash, potatoes, onions, celery, peppers, green beans and carrots may be used.

title: quick and easy cheese cake
directions: In mixer bowl, beat until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Knead flour and Crisco.
Add sugar, dissolved yeast water and buttermilk.
Roll and cut.
Let stand at least 20 minutes.
(They can stay in refrigerator overnight.)
Bake 10 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add flour, salt, pepper, sugar, sour cream and grated onion.
Fold the beans into the mixture.
Spread in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with Swiss cheese.
Top with buttered crushed cornflakes. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Cook apples 5 minutes in apple juice.
Add cornstarch, cook until thickened.
Add cinnamon. Pour mixture into pie crust, cover with other crust.
Seal edges, cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: t's corn cakes
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add milk.
Slowly add cornmeal and salt.
Mix well.
Add butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on hot well-greased griddle.
Stir batter each time a spoonful is taken out.
Brown on one side, then on the other.
Makes about 40 paper thin cakes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: oat pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients
in a food processor and
pulse until well mixed.
Press
onto
bottom
and
sides of pie pan, then add filling and bake.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix soda in hot water; stir in buttermilk.
Add salt.
Sift flour and add slowly.
Bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Wrap bread sticks with sliced bacon; cook in the microwave until bacon is crisp.
They are ready to serve.

title: potato pancakes with cheddar
directions: In a bowl beat egg, then beat in milk, salt and flour.
Add grated or chopped onion and grated cheese.
Wash and peel potatoes, then grate directly into egg mixture, working rapidly because grated potato tends to darken.

title: cream cheese cakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla with egg beater until smooth.
Place cupcake papers in tins.
Place 1 wafer in each cup.
Put 2 teaspoons on each wafer.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add topping.
Chill and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie dough according to directions.
Spread on pizza pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese (softened) with powdered sugar.
Spread over pizza.
Slice bananas over pizza.
Mix sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thick. Add dry jello.
Stir and cool.
Spread over bananas.
Add fresh fruit in a pretty pattern.
Keep in fridge.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bananas, and chill.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones and cut up.
Put the margarine, mushrooms, garlic, onions, pepper, almonds and rice into a heavy skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until rice begins to turn yellow.
Add chicken broth, which has been heated, and soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into a casserole dish, sprayed with Pam, and cover tightly.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 10.

title: tony's cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs with 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Line bottom of a spring-form pan.

title: jefferson salad
directions: Do not add water to jello.
Drain fruit well.
Mix dry jello with fruit.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: my best carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 round cake pans. Stir together first 4 ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth. Add flour mixture, beating at low speed until blended. Fold in carrots and next 3 ingredients. Pour batter into prepared cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out

clean. Drizzle Buttermilk Glaze evenly over cake. Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack. Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: good times chocolate pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons margarine; microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue to cook for 2 more minutes, stirring after each minute.
Mixture should be thick, but will thicken more as it sets.
Add the vanilla and stir into mixture. Pour into individual serving dishes.
Garnish with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to a soft ball stage. Add remaining ingredients. Blend.
Do not overblend. Pour into a 9-inch square pan and cool. Best ever peanut butter fudge!

title: maple walnut pie
directions: Partially bake pie shell for 6 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool. Cream butter and brown sugar well.
Add beaten eggs and maple syrup.
Add nuts, vanilla and salt.
Mix.
Pour into cooled shell. Bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: candy roll
directions: Mix into a roll and slice after the chill. Roll in waxed paper. Keep in refrigerator.

title: chinese chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix mayo, soy sauce and seasonings in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: orange sunshine cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch cake pan (sprayed with cooking spray).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely before adding topping.

title: broccoli cheese and rice casserole
directions: Steam broccoli to the point where it is about 2/3 done.
Cook 2 cups of rice.
Combine broccoli, rice and the entire jar of Cheez Whiz in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: garlic toast
directions: Slice bread into 1-inch slices.
Toast in broiler oven on both sides.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together margarine, minced garlic and salt to taste.
Spread mixture over cool toast.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Reheat under broiler just before serving.

title: reduced calorie cheesecake cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
On sheet of wax paper, combine flour and baking powder, set aside.
In bowl, combine all ingredients except flour mixture.
Using electric mixer, beat at medium speed until mixture forms a smooth batter, stir in flour mixture.
On nonstick cookie sheet, drop batter by rounded tablespoon forming 12 cookies (leave 1-inch between each).
Bake for 5 minutes; using a 1/4 teaspoon measure, press center of each cookie making an indentation.
Spoon spread into each indentation.
Bake until brown about 5 more minutes.
Makes 1 dozen cookies, 50 calories each.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Put pineapple, it's juice and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in gelatin and cream cheese; cool. Fold in nuts, celery, apples, and whipped topping.
Pour into 9 inch square dish.
Chill until set.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
When cake is baked, punch holes in top with fork or toothpick.
Pour condensed milk over top of cake, then pour caramel topping over condensed milk.
When cake is completely cool, spread Cool Whip over top.
Keep in refrigerator. Leave in pan it is baked in.

title: apple turtle cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and nuts together.
Stir in butter and blend well.
Put in 9-inch spring-form pan to form crust.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Toss with apples.
Pour 1/2 cheesecake mixture into crust lined pan.
Arrange 1/2 apples in concentric circle over cheesecake layer.
Pour 1/2 the remaining cheese over apples.
Arrange balance of apples over cheese layer and top with remaining cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool, then refrigerate overnight.
Arrange nuts on top of cooled cheesecake.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, pineapple with juice, sour cream and sugar in a deep, narrow bowl.
Beat slowly at low speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell and chill at least 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip, pineapple and cherries, if desired.

title: "golf ball cookie"
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, pecans, sugar, margarine and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over hot water.
Coat entire ball by dipping it into chocolate mixture, using tongs or candy dipper.
Place on wax paper to harden.
Can put decorations (sprinkles) on top before they harden.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls about size of walnut.
Pat down to shape with fork on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes. Watch closely.
They burn easily.

title: crazy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Blend all ingredients, except oil, in a blender.
Next, slowly blend in up to 2 cups of oil, depending on desired thickness.
The more oil, the thicker it will be.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: favorite squash and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil squash and onion in small amount of salted water until tender.
Drain.
While squash is cooking, prepare topping.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave for 10 minutes. Mix soup with broccoli.
Put cheese on top.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: cabbage and tomato casserole
directions: In oil or butter, saute pepper, onion and garlic, about 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes which are cut in pieces together with liquid from tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes (can be done in microwave oven).
Cook or steam cored cabbage until fairly tender.
Then chop coarsely.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup of the cracker crumbs, the onion, 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Combine the remaining 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and the remaining butter.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: delicious sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat 1 minute.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Add 4 cups flour.
Blend last cup flour slowly.
You may not need it all.
Let chill overnight; roll out 1/8-inch thick and bake until light golden brown at 350°, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes (smaller than julienne) and onion very fine. Add 1 egg; mix.
Add salt, pepper and flour.
In frying pan, add 1/4 inch oil.
When oil is hot, add 1 tablespoon mixture to oil and fry until potatoes are brown.
Turn over and fry other side. Drain on paper towel and taste.
You may need to add more salt and pepper.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix the sour cream, coconut and sugar together; leave, covered, in refrigerator overnight.

title: "kourambiethes" - powdered sugar butter cookies
directions: Beat butter 30 minutes or until light and fluffy; add 1/2 cup powdered sugar and beat well.
Add the egg yolks and continue beating.
Add vanilla and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Have powdered sugar sprinkled on a large sheet pan or paper.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top while still warm.

title: crazy crust apple or cherry pie
directions: Tip:
Mincemeat pie filling can also be used if you desire.

title: lisa's spaghetti
directions: Saute chopped onion and green pepper in a tablespoon of butter.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add 2 packages of spaghetti sauce mix.
Add diced tomatoes, Ro-Tel and tomato sauce. Add water if needed.
Stir.
Bring to a boil.
Slowly add the uncooked spaghetti noodles and stir.
Let simmer on low until noodles are cooked.
Stir frequently.
After noodles are cooked, cover and let simmer on low, stirring occasionally.
The longer it simmers, the better flavor it will have.
May be refrigerated overnight.

title: zucchini spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain fat.
Set aside.
Slice zucchini and mushrooms.
Place all ingredients and spices into crock-pot and stir.
Simmer in crock-pot for 8 hours or overnight. Serve over rice or favorite pasta.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all the dry ingredients. Then, add the oil, water, milk and syrup.
Put the mixture into a medium-size pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Heat broth and undiluted soups and pour over cornbread crumbs.
Add onions and celery.
Mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour half of dressing in greased 3-quart casserole dish. Add chicken and top with rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sage to taste and boiled eggs are optional.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut the chicken into small pieces (bone and all in about 1-inch pieces or debone, but I like with bone).
Salt and pepper over chicken and mix.
Chop onion; set aside.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix well and spread on cake.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of chopped nuts.

title: depression stew(makes 6 hearty bowls)
directions: Simmer bone, meat, onion, tomatoes, celery and spices for 2 hours.
Add potatoes and tomato sauce and continue simmering until potatoes are done.
Cut rolled pie crust into 1-inch strips.
Turn soup on high and slowly pinch 1-inch pieces off strips and drop into boiling soup, one by one.
(These pieces will turn into dumplings and thicken soup.)
When all pieces have been dropped in, stir gently and lower fire.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes.
When finished, you have a cheap pot of stew perfect for a cold day.

title: microwave easy spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart ceramic tea pot.
Heat in microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a large casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine soup, milk and mayonnaise.
In another bowl, combine rice, chicken, peas, onion and bell pepper.
Stir soup mixture into chicken mixture.
Add half the Cheddar.
Spoon into casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar.
Bake until top is golden, about 25 minutes.

title: tostada dip
directions: Layer on serving dish in order given.

title: cold slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve chilled.

title: saffron rice
directions: Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is soft.
Add broth and saffron and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cook over medium-high heat, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Turn rice and cook 10 minutes more.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon.
Add sweet potatoes while beating, mash until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in pineapple and raisins.
Spread into square or oblong baking dish.
Press marshmallows in rows halfway down into mixture. Bake at 350° until marshmallows are melted and brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Makes a delicious dip for a fresh veggie platter.

title: grandma's depression cake
directions: In a medium saucepan, simmer sugar, coffee, shortening, raisins and apple together for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool 10 minutes.
In a large bowl mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, all the spices and the nuts.
Pour sugar-raisin mixture into dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until center of cake springs back when lightly pressed with fingers.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Simmer kraut in water; drain and squeeze out all liquids. Repeat twice.
Add soup and kielbasa.
Simmer, covered, 2 hours.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix together cream cheese and dressing; spread on rye bread rounds.
Top with thinly sliced cucumbers.

title: tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except pie filling and Cool Whip.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
From each part divide into 12 walnut size pieces.
With fingers, gently press dough to form the shape of a cup.
After finishing all 4 dozen, fill each tart with a tablespoon of pie filling.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove tarts from the pan immediately.
Cool on rack. Top with dollop of Cool Whip.
Tarts may be frozen after baking. Defrost for 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate dip for strawberries
directions: Heat together the honey, cream, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add chocolate pieces; melt.
Add brandy and mix well.
Serve with whole strawberries for dipping.
Banana slices, stemmed cherries or pieces of cake doughnuts may also be served for dipping.

title: italian rum cake
directions: Line pan with 1 package anisette cookies.
Mix rum and water to make 1 cup.
Pour 1/2 cup mixture over first layer of cookies. Cook vanilla pudding and pour over the cookies.
Use second package of cookies and repeat as before, only use chocolate pudding on top.
